1
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:17,800
The legendary search
for the next top models and actors

2
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:21,440
that reshaped the Thai entertainment
and fashion industries is back.

3
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:25,680
Join me, Kim Goodburn,
on this historic new journey.

4
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,600
This is <i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4</i>.

5
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:36,080
<i>Last week's first campaign of the season</i>

6
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:38,920
<i>featured a creative runway challenge.</i>

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,760
<i>Mentor Off snatched the first victory</i>

8
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:45,360
<i>with Assistant Mentor JingJing's support.</i>

9
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:46,480
Team Off.

10
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:47,760
- Yes!
- Yes!

11
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:50,160
Two heads are better than one.
It's not fair.

12
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:52,400
Mentor Mile might be new to this game.

13
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:54,320
You know what to do now, right?

14
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,920
<i>This forced Mentor Mile and Mentor Pancake</i>

15
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,120
<i>to reluctantly send one member</i>
<i>to the Black Room.</i>

16
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:05,880
<i>Ultimately, Mentor Off eliminated Wigrom</i>
<i>from Team Pancake-Ananda.</i>

17
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:07,200
You're not The Face.

18
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:10,120
Of course, I need to know.
You sent my guy home.

19
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:12,160
My job is to eliminate, not to explain.

20
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,120
Hope your team won't mess up.

21
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:17,160
<i>Bring the heat, we'll fire back.</i>
<i>If they fight, we fight back.</i>

22
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:18,600
I'm not scared either.

23
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:51,400
<i>The winner</i>
<i>of </i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4

24
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,320
<i>will collaborate with Clear Thailand.</i>

25
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:58,560
<i>He will receive a one-year supply</i>
<i>of Clear Ice Cool Menthol.</i>

26
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:01,120
<i>And get the chance to work</i>
<i>with Vaseline Thailand.</i>

27
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:04,760
<i>Plus, he'll receive</i>
<i>Vaseline SPF50+ PA++++,</i>

28
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:08,039
<i>Gluta Hyaluronic Acid,</i>
<i>Photoage Defense UV Serum</i>

29
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,960
<i>free for an entire year.</i>

30
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,640
<i>He will also collaborate with AXE.</i>

31
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:15,440
<i>And receive a year's supply</i>
<i>of personal care products.</i>

32
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:18,920
<i>Bearbeary, only the wearers feel it.</i>

33
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,800
<i>Premium wear for every style,</i>
<i>featuring top design and innovation.</i>

34
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:25,040
<i>They'll award a 100,000-baht gift voucher.</i>

35
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:29,200
<i>Strive for perfection</i>
<i>with a membership to Hotman Fitness.</i>

36
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:32,000
<i>Including an 18-month</i>
<i>personal training program.</i>

37
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:36,000
<i>Plus a 200,000-baht package</i>
<i>from V Design Clinic.</i>

38
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:38,600
<i>Get ready to step onto the national screen</i>

39
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,640
<i>through a collaboration</i>
<i>with Channel 3 HD, Thailand.</i>

40
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:45,360
<i>And sign an acting contract</i>
<i>with Kantana Group Public Company Limited,</i>

41
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:48,320
<i>Thailand's leading producer</i>
<i>of dramas and films.</i>

42
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:40,080
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.

43
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:44,760
Welcome to <i>The Face Men Thailand</i>
<i>Season 4</i>, Episode 3.

44
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:51,440
After surviving a very challenging test,

45
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:55,000
all 14 of you remain in the competition.

46
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:58,000
Today, we're bringing you
to the master class.

47
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:00,080
In today's master class,

48
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:05,360
you'll learn a crucial skill
for every new actor.

49
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:08,320
It's about creating special moments

50
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:13,320
that make the audience believe
and remember your performance.

51
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:17,000
We call this
the "Chemistry Moment" master class.

52
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:21,760
Please give a warm welcome
to Mentor Off and Mentor Mile.

53
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:30,120
Today's instructors
are Mentor Off and Mentor Mile.

54
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:33,560
Keep your grudges to yourself.
Today, they are our teachers.

55
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,240
They will share their knowledge.

56
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:38,320
The timing is perfect because
we can stab them in the back later.

57
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,480
Why are Chemistry Moments
important in acting?

58
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,000
- Let me explain.
- Yes.

59
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,320
Many of you have probably heard this term.

60
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:50,200
We hear it a lot in modern shows, like,

61
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:52,680
"Wow, these characters
have great chemistry."

62
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:55,040
First of all, for chemistry to spark,

63
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:58,440
one person must be ready
to convey their message,

64
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:01,160
ready to communicate,

65
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:04,640
to make the other listen,
acknowledge, or feel something.

66
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:07,960
It could be through eye contact,
physical touch,

67
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:11,520
or just silently looking at each other.

68
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:14,560
Whatever your intention is,
the receiver must feel it.

69
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:16,680
When you react to one another,

70
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:18,680
that's when chemistry is created.

71
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:21,560
Basically, you need to stay focused.

72
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:25,080
Be focused and present in the moment.
Know exactly what you're doing.

73
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:28,880
To develop the on-screen chemistry,

74
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:32,320
you should focus entirely
on your scene partner.

75
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,080
Stay true to your character.

76
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:37,520
Be present, stay in the moment,
and take it slow.

77
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:42,920
Feel exactly what your character feels,
and the chemistry will happen naturally.

78
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:47,040
I'm glad to be learning acting.
It's a completely new experience for me.

79
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:50,040
I've always wanted to learn,
and I'm very interested.

80
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:52,720
To make sure you understand

81
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:56,720
how to connect and create
a Chemistry Moment,

82
00:05:56,800 --> 00:06:00,120
I want all 14 of you to pair up.

83
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,480
But you can't pair up with your teammates.

84
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,920
It's another challenge to see

85
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,520
how we adapt
to different people and situations.

86
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,200
I'm so excited about this pairing.

87
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,960
All right, pick your partner.

88
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,560
I already had someone in mind.

89
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:18,040
It had to be <i>Oppa</i>.

90
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:22,080
I called him over. He was nearby.

91
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:27,000
<i>I don't know if this is a blessing</i>
<i>or a curse, but I'm paired with Peem.</i>

92
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,880
He told us to find a partner.

93
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,360
I was coughing.

94
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,160
I turned around
and ended up paired with him.

95
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:35,080
Like Mentor Mile said earlier,

96
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,120
acting requires focus.

97
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:40,520
Try not to laugh while making eye contact.

98
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:44,640
If either of you laughs,

99
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:48,240
your pair is out.

100
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:51,400
This is a focus test to see
if you can become the character.

101
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:54,320
How well can you detach from yourselves?

102
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:58,560
Those who can detach
and be the character won't laugh at all.

103
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:01,360
I'm just happy to be learning this.

104
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,720
Acting with friends
can be pretty funny too.

105
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:06,320
If you're ready, begin.

106
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:10,840
<i>Today, they taught us</i>
<i>how to create a moment of chemistry.</i>

107
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,840
<i>How to stay in that moment.</i>

108
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:16,640
<i>Stay focused</i>
<i>and observe what they're doing.</i>

109
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:21,320
Whatever they give me,
I try to receive it and respond.

110
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:24,800
<i>I don't get it either.</i>

111
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,960
You two, out. Go.

112
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,960
- Sit down.
- Why did you laugh?

113
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,160
<i>He said my face is funny.</i>

114
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,880
<i>Like I had something in my mouth,</i>
<i>which I did not.</i>

115
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:38,360
<i>But when I looked at him,</i>
<i>he had already lost it.</i>

116
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,760
He was holding it in,
which made me laugh too.

117
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:42,520
So I completely lost my focus.

118
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,800
Off, come look at him.

119
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:46,680
He's laughing so hard he's crying.

120
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,480
Are you happy or sad right now?

121
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:50,040
Both.

122
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:50,960
Very sad.

123
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:51,880
Very sad.

124
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,360
- You two, out.
- Take a seat.

125
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,640
<i>Lincoln, he's so handsome. I laughed.</i>

126
00:07:55,720 --> 00:08:00,000
Laughed until I cried. Like this.

127
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,520
Jacob really tried.

128
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:06,040
When I looked at him,
he couldn't hold it either.

129
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:08,800
I laughed
because he's so handsome, I cried.

130
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,200
You two are friends, right?

131
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,880
- Are you guys close?
- Yes, we are.

132
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,480
Oh, that explains it.

133
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,800
I thought we would have
best friend chemistry.

134
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:19,920
I thought so too,
but when we made eye contact…

135
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,560
Oh man, I'm dead.

136
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:22,560
I can't.

137
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:26,440
If I had more time,
I think I could stay focused.

138
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:29,040
I could hold the laugh. Yes.

139
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:32,039
<i>You have to do it within the time limit.</i>

140
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,120
<i>Practice at home if you need more time.</i>

141
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,760
<i>We want you to do it right now.</i>

142
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,880
So you must do it right now.

143
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:41,960
Not even five seconds in,
and I lost two members from two pairs.

144
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,520
Man, I'm secretly worried.

145
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,240
It can be a little stressful.

146
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:50,280
For step two, I want everyone

147
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,040
to take one step forward.

148
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:55,280
<i>At first, I tried to feel nothing</i>
<i>and stay in the present.</i>

149
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:58,360
<i>But looking at Rome up close,</i>

150
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:01,680
<i>I felt like</i>
<i>I had never been this close to a guy.</i>

151
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,920
<i>I felt he was very charming.</i>

152
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,040
<i>I thought he looked like a doll.</i>

153
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:09,120
<i>But what kind of doll is this tall?</i>
<i>Then I laughed.</i>

154
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,840
But…

155
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,240
I didn't smile at all.
I didn't break the rules.

156
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,360
Enough. You're out.

157
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,600
Stop, you can't hold back anymore.

158
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,080
I can't.

159
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,320
<i>I found it funny.</i>

160
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,600
But if I get a chance,
I want to do better.

161
00:09:22,680 --> 00:09:24,960
I will add another challenge.

162
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,520
This time, touch each other.

163
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,880
It's up to you which part to touch.

164
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:30,720
- Don't be shy.
- Here is fine.

165
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:34,000
Don't overthink it. Just touch their body.

166
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,480
<i>At first, I was tense and almost laughed.</i>

167
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:39,160
But okay, I let it go.

168
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:41,960
I had to focus on the person
in front, Kimhan.

169
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,760
Let me add a bit more of a challenge.

170
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,960
Use a part other than your hands to touch.

171
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,240
- Can I pause for a sec?
- Sure.

172
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:51,280
- I don't like this pair.
- Anything but hands!

173
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,000
I didn't use my hands.

174
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,360
Okay, let's show them.

175
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,680
The chemistry comes from…

176
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,200
Feet. I can't hold it too!

177
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:02,160
<i>Many pairs were playing around.</i>
<i>Off and I were being lenient.</i>

178
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:05,040
<i>But the real job won't be.</i>
<i>I didn't really like it.</i>

179
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:09,160
But ultimately, you're the ones
who bear the consequences.

180
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,360
So I let it slide.

181
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,680
This time.

182
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:15,720
Once your feet meet,
slowly touch your hands together.

183
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,200
Keep it going, don't stop.

184
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:21,000
Touch anywhere, however you want.
Keep it going.

185
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:23,440
But the technique
is to stay with your desire.

186
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,680
Keep eye contact.

187
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,800
Imagine whatever you want,
but keep your hands moving.

188
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,200
Touch them.

189
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,360
<i>Don't stop. Keep going.</i>

190
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:33,600
<i>I didn't think about Pom's gender.</i>

191
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:36,600
<i>I just saw him as a person.</i>
<i>What is he doing?</i>

192
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:38,760
What is he feeling?
What does he think of me?

193
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:41,760
<i>I didn't expect it to turn out well.</i>
<i>Pom exceeded expectations.</i>

194
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:44,160
<i>We fed off each other's emotions.</i>

195
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:46,920
<i>Touching the face, the arm… Wow, it was…</i>

196
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,920
We really had chemistry.

197
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:52,520
That's enough.
This pair feels like a bickering couple.

198
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,080
This pair is cute.

199
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:56,280
They're friends experimenting
with something new.

200
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,960
Yes, trying something new.

201
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,920
- These two act like a real couple.
- Something like that.

202
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,680
<i>I really liked Kimhan and Pom.</i>

203
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:04,280
<i>They were the most focused.</i>

204
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:07,560
<i>They might be the best pair here.</i>

205
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,760
Absolutely perfect for these two.

206
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,520
All right, everyone.

207
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:16,160
You just learned how to build a connection
between scene partners

208
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:18,600
to create a moment of chemistry.

209
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:21,120
Now, it's time for the main challenge

210
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,880
of today's master class.

211
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:27,960
Today, we have a very special guest
presenting the challenge.

212
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,920
She represents a brand
that has cared for Thai skin for years.

213
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Please give a big round of applause

214
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:36,000
for Maiprae, Ruthaipat Surachaidungthavin,

215
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:39,000
Vaseline Thailand's Brand Manager.

216
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:43,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

217
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,440
RUTHAIPAT SURACHAIDUNGTHAVIN
VASELINE THAILAND'S BRAND MANAGER

218
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,960
Today, on behalf of Vaseline Thailand,

219
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:53,840
I invite you all
to challenge the sun together

220
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:56,600
with the theme "Sun Up, Glow On."

221
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,440
For today's master class challenge,

222
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,640
- you'll walk an outdoor runway,
- Yes.

223
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:04,440
a playground-themed runway.

224
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:08,680
Everyone must have at least
one signature pose

225
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:11,800
to present yourselves as Vaseline Men.

226
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:16,360
Be unique, confident,
and make the sun surrender.

227
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:19,560
<i>It's another runway.</i>
<i>Part of me is confident I can pull it off.</i>

228
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:22,640
But I can't let my guard down.

229
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:25,760
I've won a lot, so people are waiting
for me to slip up.

230
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:27,800
- Our runway is outdoors, right?
- Right.

231
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:30,800
I'm afraid your skin might get damaged,

232
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:33,160
becoming dull and dry.

233
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:36,600
Today, Vaseline Thailand
comes with a brand-new product.

234
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:42,840
It's the Gluta-Hya
Photoage Defense SPF50 PA++++.

235
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:47,080
You'll all apply it
before hitting the runway

236
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,920
to protect your beautiful skin
from damage.

237
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,560
To prove that our product really works,

238
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:59,360
you'll apply a Vaseline tattoo
anywhere on your body.

239
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:03,480
This will test
if the skin under the tattoo

240
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:07,480
gets dark after going outdoors
once you peel it off.

241
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,920
Not only is the challenge tough,

242
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:14,560
but you also have to present
glowing, radiant skin

243
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:16,920
while braving the sun.

244
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,160
What are the judging criteria for today?

245
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,480
I'll look at the overall picture

246
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:25,720
of each team's show

247
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,520
to see who performs better.

248
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:31,520
Show your true self, your brightness,
and your character.

249
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:34,680
And create the most creative poses.

250
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:38,200
<i>I'm not stressed, just a bit worried.</i>

251
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,680
I just want to do a good job.

252
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:43,040
It's exciting. This show is never easy.

253
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:44,560
It's meant to be challenging.

254
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,600
Not just anyone can do it.

255
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,360
But I tell myself I can.

256
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:52,200
You've heard the challenge and criteria.

257
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,520
Now, go prepare yourselves to prove

258
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,360
who can "Sun Up" and "Glow On" the best.

259
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:58,360
Please get ready.

260
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,080
I'm full of energy today.

261
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:05,920
I'll give it my all. I won't slack off.

262
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:09,000
I'm always confident.
Win or lose, I have to give 100%.

263
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,480
I won the last master class.

264
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,400
This one is a runway again.

265
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:15,880
I'm hopeful I can pull it off.
I'm confident.

266
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,080
With the "Sun Up, Glow On" challenge.

267
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:31,240
Contestants must design
an outdoor runway walk

268
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:35,760
and creatively handle
the obstacles in their way.

269
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:36,760
Is everyone ready?

270
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:37,960
- Ready.
- Ready.

271
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:41,440
Let's start with the first group.

272
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:42,520
First group, please.

273
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,360
This is our first group.

274
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:46,960
Gluf, Leo, and PP.

275
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,920
Oh, they framed it here.

276
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:53,200
Everything happened so fast.
No time to prepare.

277
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:56,520
They look a bit unsure, though.

278
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,960
- Not really.
- Yes.

279
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,640
Ever since he walked out.

280
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,600
- Since he walked out, it's like…
- Like he's overthinking.

281
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:03,680
Yes.

282
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:05,160
First up, Gluf.

283
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:08,320
He needs more confidence.
He might lack experience.

284
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:12,240
So he's unsure. "Should I act confident?"

285
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:15,680
"Or how do I project that confidence?"

286
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:18,280
He didn't really do much.

287
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:21,440
Being the first,
I didn't see anyone else walk.

288
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,240
I wasn't sure if my walk was right.

289
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:27,160
So I wasn't very confident during my walk.

290
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,880
The brief is actually pretty tough.

291
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,400
The floor is made of foam.

292
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:35,600
It sinks when you walk on it.

293
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:37,280
We didn't even get to rehearse.

294
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:40,280
And we had so little time
to plan together.

295
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,160
Man, I was so nervous.

296
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,880
Don't let his muscles distract us.

297
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,560
Hey, that doesn't look good.

298
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,880
There were a few mistakes.

299
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:07,520
But in terms of Leo's creativity,
was it enough?

300
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:10,400
For me, it was.
Because he posed really well.

301
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,920
He's selling the product.

302
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:16,880
His poses were more creative
than the other two.

303
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,200
- Yes.
- A little bit.

304
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:22,840
- Wait. Is that it?
- Just like that?

305
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,520
Wait, Leo!

306
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:25,680
- That's it?
- Seriously?

307
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:28,720
Leo, one pose is just not enough.

308
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:31,640
He had multiple chances,
but he just walked once and left.

309
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,800
The brief was "Signature One Pose," right?

310
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:36,520
But there's no limit.
He could've done more if he wanted.

311
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,960
Just one signature pose.

312
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,840
- Right.
- But you could've done five other poses.

313
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:41,760
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

314
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,960
It comes down to
how he interpreted the brief.

315
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:47,600
This group's overall energy is pretty low.

316
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:51,280
And looking at them individually,
you can see their insecurities.

317
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:52,840
In all of them.

318
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,000
True.

319
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:56,160
It felt like their fire just wasn't there.

320
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,960
They seemed anxious.

321
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,240
They didn't have a storyline of…

322
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,240
- Presenting.
- A fun playground.

323
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:06,240
Yes, they were just thinking,
"I need to walk here and stand there."

324
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:09,160
So I feel they lacked inner energy.

325
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,800
I believe with that limited time…

326
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:15,160
I don't think I did too badly.
But lacking confidence made it…

327
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,760
Let's move on to the next group.

328
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:20,119
Group two, come on out.

329
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:22,240
Okay, our second group.

330
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:24,359
Bonus, Lincoln, and Mew.

331
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:27,079
I was a little nervous at first.

332
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:28,760
Once I walked out…

333
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,800
Oh, wow.

334
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,960
- That's sick.
- Not bad.

335
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,400
Not bad at all.

336
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,800
Nice.

337
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,600
Bonus looks like he's putting in effort.

338
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:50,800
Seeing his improvement,
I feel like he can tackle anything.

339
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:51,880
He wants to win.

340
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:53,600
It was pretty tough.

341
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,720
I wasn't sure if it looked good or not.

342
00:17:55,800 --> 00:18:00,520
Because we were so rushed.
We barely had time to practice.

343
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:06,480
But if it were me,
I would show the Vaseline logo.

344
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,760
Instead of just showing my head like that.

345
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:10,640
Right.

346
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:15,120
It was okay,
but he didn't really utilize the space.

347
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,720
Did he forget to grab the product?

348
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,120
- He forgot.
- Did he forget?

349
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,360
I told them to stay focused.
Why didn't he?

350
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:27,080
Listen, calm down.

351
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,560
I don't know why he rushed.

352
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,960
They had the same amount of time.
How did he forget?

353
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,120
I forgot to grab the product.

354
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:35,040
But I grabbed it at the end.

355
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,720
I just held it like this.

356
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,280
Bam. See that?

357
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,800
I can't do anything
if the client doesn't like it.

358
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:41,880
It's too late.

359
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:44,560
Grabbing the product at the end
was just too late.

360
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,000
You know what I mean?

361
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:48,480
Gives me a headache.

362
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:51,960
I wanted to see some fun,
inner fire, and youthfulness.

363
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:56,840
I wanted them to use the whole space.
Everyone's energy felt so flat.

364
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:58,840
- No energy.
- They didn't give it all.

365
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:01,680
- Totally agree.
- Okay.

366
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:04,320
Everyone felt pretty distant.
There was no drive.

367
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,360
Overall, this team is not good enough.

368
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:09,400
They don't meet the standard.
I don't even want to watch.

369
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:11,560
Let's bring out the third group.

370
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:14,680
As mentioned, the theme
is "Sun Up, Glow On."

371
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,840
So you need to glow.

372
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,640
- My team took off their shirts.
- That's the team strategy?

373
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,240
Seriously?

374
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:23,240
I just realized my team gets hot easily.

375
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:25,280
Just took them off. Great bodies, though.

376
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:29,960
I feel that adding movement
makes us stand out.

377
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:32,840
But doing too much might look fake.

378
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:35,200
I would rather keep it balanced.

379
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:37,560
Wow, great opening.

380
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:40,680
Manyoo was good.

381
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:42,760
Manyoo was great.
He looked more determined.

382
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,280
He's showing great improvement.

383
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:50,120
My group didn't have time to talk.
There was no time for a brief.

384
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:51,480
Time was really tight.

385
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:54,920
Extraordinary.

386
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:55,880
Pretty good.

387
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:02,040
Oh, he's highlighting the "Vaseline" logo.

388
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,280
Not holding the product

389
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:06,520
- isn't a weakness at all.
- Yes, true.

390
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:09,960
I planned from the start
that I wouldn't hold the product.

391
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:11,680
I saw everyone else holding it.

392
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:15,280
So I decided not to.
I highlighted the "Vaseline" logo.

393
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:17,640
Oh, wow.

394
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:20,240
Pom did better than expected.

395
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:23,040
He definitely stood out on this team.

396
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:25,640
He gave it his all. He had fun and smiled.

397
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:28,280
Great poses. Everything was perfect.

398
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:31,080
So, I think Pom did a great job.

399
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:35,240
I was confident.
I already knew what to do.

400
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,480
I just followed my plan.

401
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:39,600
- Careful!
- Oh, no!

402
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:42,120
It was slippery because of the rain.

403
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,320
So I slipped and bumped my foot.

404
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:47,920
I'm a bit bummed. I feel like I failed.

405
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:51,680
I feel for him.
But if you're not sure, don't do it.

406
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:55,240
Donut just chose the upper level.
If you're unsure, don't do it.

407
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:58,040
Getting hurt is just an excuse.

408
00:20:58,120 --> 00:20:59,760
I don't think it was a mistake.

409
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:02,920
But misinterpreting the theme
and having the wrong energy…

410
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,840
were the real mistakes.

411
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,960
Fox, you make me sleepy.
That's my first comment.

412
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,400
How can you make me sleepy?

413
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,640
Your poses weren't bad.

414
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:18,400
- But your energy was.
- He's creative.

415
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,320
Right.

416
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:21,800
You looked totally lifeless.

417
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:25,600
I'll give you points
for the creative poses.

418
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:26,800
But your inner energy…

419
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:28,880
just wasn't fun, Fox.

420
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:30,000
You looked bored.

421
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,480
I think anything can happen.

422
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:35,040
I did my best.
Let's just wait for the results.

423
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,720
Let's see how this team's final shots are.

424
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,600
Hey.

425
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:45,720
Damn!

426
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:46,920
I like it.

427
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,600
I quite like the third group.

428
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:53,280
- They spread out nicely. Good overall.
- Good.

429
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,960
The final group.

430
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:58,000
This group includes…

431
00:21:58,080 --> 00:21:59,320
Rome, Kimhan,

432
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,880
Peem, and Jacob.

433
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:05,960
My "Sun Up, Glow On"
is bright and cheerful.

434
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:08,600
It shows off my playfulness.

435
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:13,800
My pose involved grabbing the pole
to show off my physique.

436
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,040
I also held the product
to display it a bit.

437
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:21,920
This theme wasn't too hard for me.

438
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,480
It's right up my alley.

439
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,360
I think I nailed the brief.

440
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:29,000
Kimhan did fine.

441
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:31,520
But he lacked confidence.

442
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,400
It showed in his poses and his eyes.

443
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,000
It was good, but not sharp enough.

444
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:40,160
They told us to be playful.

445
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:43,480
So I decided to act like a monkey.

446
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,080
I decided to swing.

447
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,400
To show my playful side.

448
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,000
While keeping it manly.

449
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,320
Hey!

450
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,480
Creative!

451
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:53,400
- How's this pose?
- Nice.

452
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,680
Nice.

453
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:55,600
Nice.

454
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:58,960
His presentation and creativity
make Jacob the number one for me.

455
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:01,800
My only complaint
is when he squeezed the lotion…

456
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,720
and tossed the product away.

457
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:06,880
If I were the client,
I wouldn't be okay with that.

458
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:11,600
Yes.

459
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,800
Here comes Michael Jackson.

460
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:16,240
I liked Peem the most on this team.

461
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:19,160
I think he's really confident.

462
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:22,920
He has ideas and the courage
to execute the poses.

463
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,560
And confidence to present them.

464
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:28,240
I wanted to stand on the blue barrel.

465
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:29,360
But on the first step…

466
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,360
Shit!

467
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:34,800
At that moment,
I thought, "No, don't fall yet."

468
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:37,680
I already tripped,
but the show must go on.

469
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,840
Despite the mistake, he bounced back.

470
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:41,400
I could overlook that mistake.

471
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:44,400
I think Peem did well here.

472
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,160
- Really well.
- Good.

473
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:50,080
Peem was the standout for me today.

474
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:53,280
He boldly opened the product
and poured it.

475
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:55,520
It formed a beautiful stream.

476
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:57,240
I have to give it to him.

477
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:02,840
The last team was fun,
though some lost focus a bit.

478
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,640
- But the team did well.
- Yes.

479
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:06,520
As for their final group pose…

480
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:09,040
Kimhan, about his pose…

481
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,320
Personally, I wasn't a fan.

482
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,280
It didn't suit the product.

483
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:16,120
Should it be like this? Or like this?

484
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,880
Anything but that.

485
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:21,400
Like a mannequin.

486
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:25,360
All right, let's take a look
at the final poses of all four teams.

487
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,680
I think this is very challenging.

488
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,000
They use the space well.

489
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:39,960
- This one is just right.
- This is okay.

490
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:42,200
I must commend all 14 of them.

491
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:44,320
They managed themselves really well.

492
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:48,040
They figured out their own blocking.
And it was all decided on the spot.

493
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:50,520
Pulling that off was already impressive.

494
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,480
We just saw the contestants perform.

495
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:59,760
They showed their creativity
and gave it their all.

496
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:04,120
They overcame the obstacles
under the blazing sun.

497
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,800
Now, let's hear
from our judge and mentors.

498
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,680
Maiprae, what do you think?

499
00:25:09,760 --> 00:25:11,800
For the first team,

500
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:15,400
I was really looking forward to seeing
how they would interpret the brief.

501
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:18,120
They actually did a good job
utilizing the space.

502
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,280
It was okay.

503
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:21,920
But as mentioned,
their energy was very low.

504
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,480
Maybe because they went first.

505
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:25,200
They might have been a bit timid.

506
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:27,520
- So the performance fell flat.
- Right.

507
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:28,480
The second team?

508
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:32,920
I didn't even look at the details.
The overall picture just wasn't it.

509
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:36,680
It might be their creative interpretation
of the brief.

510
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:38,840
Their presentation lacked clarity.

511
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:41,240
So it didn't work. It didn't stand out.

512
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,520
What about the third team?

513
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,360
I liked them too.
Once they started having fun…

514
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:49,480
They drew me in,
and I stopped looking for flaws.

515
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:52,480
I just enjoyed it.
I knew what you were trying to convey.

516
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:55,800
You did a great job,
and the ending was fantastic.

517
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:58,840
In fact, their ending
might be my favorite.

518
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:03,200
And now, we're down to the final team.

519
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:04,840
What are your thoughts on them?

520
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:07,920
Their overall energy was similar
to the third team.

521
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:13,880
They seemed to be having fun
in bringing out their playful side.

522
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:17,560
Many of them presented
the product quite well.

523
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:20,120
I really liked it. It was good.

524
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:22,160
But they could have been more consistent.

525
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:26,160
All right, we've just heard
the feedback from our judge

526
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:27,880
and mentors.

527
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:32,680
The winner of today's
"Sun Up, Glow On" master class…

528
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:34,480
What will they receive from Vaseline?

529
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:38,160
Today's "Sun Up, Glow On"
master class winner

530
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:41,080
- will receive an Ice Bath package…
- Oh, wow!

531
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,360
worth 15,000 baht.

532
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:49,320
Plus, a year's supply of Vaseline,
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50 PA++++,

533
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:53,480
for the winner to use for a full year.

534
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:55,400
All right, Maiprae.

535
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:56,960
It's time to find out

536
00:26:57,040 --> 00:27:01,680
which of the four teams
stood out the most.

537
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:04,200
It's really hard to choose.
I can't decide.

538
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:06,160
Can I pick two teams?

539
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:10,080
Sure. So, which two teams
stood out the most?

540
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:13,040
It would be Team C and Team B.

541
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:18,960
When my team was called,
I had to be in there. I deserved a spot.

542
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:23,240
Since there were so many people,
I had a feeling it might be me.

543
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:24,400
I was secretly hoping.

544
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:30,080
Who are the top three performers
in your eyes, Maiprae?

545
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:34,440
For Team C, the two best performers

546
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:39,280
are Manyoo, who was bright
and full of great energy…

547
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:40,400
I was very impressed.

548
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,480
And Pom.

549
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:44,320
- Pom was great.
- Yes.

550
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:47,200
He conveyed his energy really well.

551
00:27:47,280 --> 00:27:50,200
He also made me feel like…

552
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:53,400
he was genuinely playing on a playground.

553
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:56,160
- It made the show fun to watch.
- Right.

554
00:27:56,240 --> 00:28:01,160
The last person who performed well
and won the judge over is

555
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,960
Peem.

556
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:06,800
What? How did I get chosen?

557
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,000
I was so confused.

558
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:10,560
I went with the flow
and ended up in the top three?

559
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:12,200
If you're confused, so am I.

560
00:28:12,280 --> 00:28:13,960
I'm baffled too.

561
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:16,400
Peem, I loved your energy.

562
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:18,440
You're bold and proactive.

563
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:22,320
Sure, there were minor slips,
but I can overlook them.

564
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,000
Because the energy he projected…

565
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,000
- Good.
- Powerful.

566
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,200
Powerful, right?

567
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:30,200
I think we all saw it.
He owned that stage.

568
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:33,880
In my head, I hoped to win.
Just a little hope.

569
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,320
I want that year's supply of Vaseline.

570
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:40,160
This is it. I'm bringing
the victory home for my mentor.

571
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:43,120
At least we have two out of three spots.

572
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,760
I was on the verge of euphoria.

573
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:48,520
I was feeling really confident
at that moment.

574
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:52,760
So, who is the winner
of today's master class, Maiprae?

575
00:28:52,840 --> 00:28:56,640
The winner of this master class is…

576
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,000
Pom!

577
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:06,720
Can I dance? I'm still over the moon.

578
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:12,280
Like I said, I got my chance,
and I won't let it go to waste.

579
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:14,240
I'll give it my all. Trust me.

580
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:16,680
I'm so proud of my team.

581
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:19,920
I've never regretted picking any of them.

582
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:22,720
I would like to thank Maiprae very much

583
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:25,280
for joining our master class today.

584
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,480
- Thank you.
- Seriously?

585
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:27,480
Thank you.

586
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:29,160
Was all that necessary?

587
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:30,760
Thank you.

588
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:34,200
All right, that's a wrap
for our master class.

589
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:37,560
Stay tuned to see
what the next campaign brings.

590
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:45,560
As for the next campaign,
my team is ready. Don't worry.

591
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:49,360
We'll do what's never been done before.

592
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:51,360
To win every single campaign.

593
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:52,520
We can do it.

594
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:56,320
Team Milestone
will definitely win the next one.

595
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:58,400
Just watch us.

596
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:02,640
All we need is your support.
Please cheer for us.

597
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,680
I'm at ACTS Studio today.

598
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:14,880
So I have to act bigger than ever.

599
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:18,120
Today might be about swimming.

600
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:19,600
Shirts off?

601
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:21,600
No way.

602
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,480
For today's campaign…

603
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:30,560
I don't care about the pool.
But all the guys would be shirtless.

604
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:31,920
Now I'm happy.

605
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:40,760
Hello, everyone.

606
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:41,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

607
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:44,920
Welcome to today's campaign.

608
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:47,840
Mentors, please come hear
your brief together.

609
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:51,120
Mentor Ananda, Mentor Off,
and Mentor Mile.

610
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,840
- Hello.
- Hello.

611
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:00,240
- Hello.
- Hello.

612
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:02,760
Mentor Off isn't alone again.

613
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:04,840
- Again? Again?
- Again?

614
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:06,720
I brought Joong Archen…

615
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:09,320
because he knows fashion films.

616
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:11,440
He's even been to Fashion Week.

617
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:13,160
Is it bad I want my team to be good?

618
00:31:13,840 --> 00:31:15,880
I don't know how he's proud of winning.

619
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:19,520
But if that's how Off is,
I guess it's fine.

620
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:22,760
I just have to deal with it.

621
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:28,160
Winning is one thing,
but what the kids learn is another.

622
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:32,720
Off, please communicate
with the crew more.

623
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:34,520
The cameraman has to shoot twice.

624
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:36,640
The creative has to be briefed twice.

625
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:39,520
Have some respect. Apologies to the crew.

626
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:43,040
Wait, I thought it was usually
Ananda and Pancake.

627
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:46,040
No, you've got it wrong.
We don't come together.

628
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:48,320
- Oh, one at a time?
- I have to babysit my child.

629
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:52,480
The schedule didn't work,
so I had Pancake help out.

630
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:53,640
We're not tag-teaming.

631
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:55,400
Oh, I didn't know.

632
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:58,120
You're cheating again.
Come on, Mile. Let's team up.

633
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,120
No way!

634
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:02,200
It's okay, Off.
Next time, I'll bring the whole film crew.

635
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,400
I'll bring everyone.

636
00:32:03,480 --> 00:32:05,480
Go for it, sir.

637
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:08,040
Come on, sit with me.

638
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:09,120
Can I sit here too?

639
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,280
- May I?
- Sure!

640
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,160
If it's not in the rules…

641
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:14,320
- That means we can get an assistant.
- Yeah.

642
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:16,560
See? I told you.
I'll bring the whole team.

643
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:18,800
- He'll bring them.
- Bring film directors.

644
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:23,320
All right. I'm sure you've all noticed
the pool to my right.

645
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,800
That means for today's campaign,

646
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:28,320
we'll be shooting underwater.

647
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:32,680
Let's meet the person
who'll give us today's brief.

648
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:34,800
Tim, Punsiri Siriwetchapun,

649
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,960
Thailand's leading fashion photographer.

650
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:41,400
PHANSIRI SIRIVEJCHAPHAN
THAILAND'S LEADING FASHION PHOTOGRAPHER

651
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,360
- Which way?
- Hello.

652
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:43,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

653
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:46,520
Tim, what's the brief
for today's campaign?

654
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:50,280
This campaign is "Spirit of Unity."
It's an underwater fashion video.

655
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:54,160
I want to capture
the act of sharing one's breath.

656
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,400
That sounds tough.

657
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:59,320
I want to see your chemistry
communicated underwater.

658
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:01,800
One person dives down and runs out of air.

659
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:06,000
I want a moment where
the other person shares their breath.

660
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:07,680
I want that magic moment.

661
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:09,960
Sharing breath…

662
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:11,680
Is it like…

663
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,120
K-I-S-S?

664
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:16,080
Okay, they obviously want us to kiss.

665
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:23,360
- Wait, is this in pairs?
- Yes, in pairs.

666
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,320
Within the team?

667
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:26,200
No, we're mixing teams.

668
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,040
Wow!

669
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:32,000
Let's have some challenge today.

670
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:33,320
My voice just cracked.

671
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:37,720
The hardest part is if two people
aren't on the same page.

672
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:40,040
If they can't agree, it's hard.

673
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,280
Just hypothetically,

674
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:45,680
if we mix teams,
how are you going to pick the winner?

675
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:46,840
It's like this.

676
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:51,240
Whoever makes me feel the connection most,
that video will win.

677
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:54,560
But for the actual winner,
we'll pick the best individual.

678
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:56,320
Oh, it's individual too.

679
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:59,480
- The best performer wins it for the team?
- Correct.

680
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:02,040
Out of the two people in the shot,
we'll pick one.

681
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:04,000
- Pick one of the two.
- Okay.

682
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:07,240
The boys are still having fun
since our team hasn't lost yet.

683
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,560
So the mood is good.

684
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:12,080
Let's see how well
they can use that mood today.

685
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:13,480
For this campaign,

686
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:16,560
each team's Mentor
will have only 25 minutes

687
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:17,960
to train their members.

688
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:21,600
Mentors can consult Tim

689
00:34:21,679 --> 00:34:25,639
while the members practice on land
for only five minutes.

690
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:28,320
But during the entire shoot today,

691
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:31,679
Mentors can only coach their own members.

692
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:35,400
The best pair will be the winning pair.

693
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:41,360
And the best individual in that pair
will win today's campaign.

694
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:43,600
Mentor Mile, Gluf is missing today, right?

695
00:34:43,679 --> 00:34:46,719
- Yes.
- Gluf can't join the campaign today

696
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:48,400
due to health reasons.

697
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:49,920
Therefore, today,

698
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:54,560
Mentor Mile must choose one member
to perform this campaign twice.

699
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:56,880
Mentor Mile, who do you choose?

700
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:59,240
I have someone. A true Moken child.

701
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:02,280
He's been in a series.

702
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,000
He eats and lives in the water.

703
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:05,640
It's Peem.

704
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:10,880
Okay, Peem.
You'll have to do this campaign twice.

705
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:13,400
I'll give it my all for both my partners.

706
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:15,760
Let's see which one turns out best.

707
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:19,160
All right.
Now, it's time to pair everyone up.

708
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,360
Pom, you won the last master class.

709
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:24,240
You get to pick your partner first.

710
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,120
Who do you want to pair with?

711
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:30,520
It's stressful deciding
who to pick as a partner.

712
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:32,840
I choose Kimhan.

713
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:38,800
I think Kimhan will be my best match

714
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,640
out of the options I had in mind.

715
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:43,200
Peem and Manyoo.

716
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:46,960
Since you placed second
and third in the last master class,

717
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:48,880
you'll play rock paper scissors

718
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:51,120
to see who gets to pick first.

719
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:54,560
- Rock paper scissors!
- Rock paper scissors!

720
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:57,560
- Rock paper scissors!
- Rock paper scissors!

721
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:00,240
Okay, Manyoo.
Who do you want to pair with?

722
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:01,520
Fox.

723
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:03,760
- Fox?
- Manyoo and Fox.

724
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,640
- Okay.
- Smart move.

725
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:08,280
If we have plenty of time, I think

726
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:11,000
we should get intimate underwater
as much as possible.

727
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,240
There might be a spark.

728
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:15,600
Or Manyoo had a certain reason
for choosing me.

729
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,560
I choose…

730
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:20,280
- PP.
- Okay.

731
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,200
Okay.

732
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:22,760
- Peem and PP.
- I'll be honest…

733
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,120
PP has real potential.

734
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:26,720
Peem is already a strong swimmer.

735
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:30,720
Since I can't swim, he'll outshine me.
I'll be totally overshadowed.

736
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:32,920
As for the other contestants,

737
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:36,680
the staff will choose
who you'll be paired with.

738
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:39,400
The first pair is Donut and Bonus.

739
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,520
Whoa.

740
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:42,640
Nice, nice.

741
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:46,040
Can I get someone else?
When our mustaches touch, it'll be weird.

742
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:47,720
And I got the only guy with one.

743
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:50,000
But if you really want to see it,
I'll do it.

744
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:53,560
The second pair is Rome and Jacob.

745
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:55,320
Okay.

746
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:57,760
Rome is my partner. I know we can do this.

747
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:01,320
We're both skilled enough
to work together.

748
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:04,520
The third pair is Lincoln and Leo.

749
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:06,880
This pair is so hot.

750
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,120
They're so handsome.

751
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:11,320
We have never worked together.

752
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:12,440
It's interesting.

753
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:18,360
And our final pair is Peem and Mew.

754
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,600
This is Mew's mission.

755
00:37:20,680 --> 00:37:24,320
We're sending Mew to do
whatever it takes to exhaust Peem.

756
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:28,840
I will make Peem feel like
he climbed a mountain and back.

757
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:32,160
Come on, let's go.

758
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,800
For this lesson,

759
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:39,040
I prepared a backstory for everyone
to use as a guideline.

760
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:41,600
But everyone should follow
their own needs.

761
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:43,000
- Hello, Tim.
- Hello, Mile.

762
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:44,440
- I'm here to help.
- Hello.

763
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:45,400
Hi.

764
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,280
- I have a question first.
- All right.

765
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:50,040
How long do you want to see them perform?

766
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:53,760
In the end, it's just a brief moment
in the final video.

767
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:56,000
You have to be able to explore

768
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:58,120
until I see the right moment.

769
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,440
Tim is so kind to help.

770
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:04,000
Nothing contradicts
what we're trying to do.

771
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:07,720
A "beauty shot" here means
you have to perform openly.

772
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:10,200
Maybe add some graceful movements.

773
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:11,800
This is the main camera.

774
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:12,800
- This one.
- Right.

775
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:15,600
As for blocking, see these four squares?

776
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:17,560
Try to stay within them.

777
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:19,520
- That way, you'll stay in frame.
- Okay.

778
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:21,440
Three minutes left.

779
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:25,400
Twenty-five minutes
for four people is too short.

780
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:29,040
I want them to understand the emotion
rather than just memorize poses.

781
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:31,040
Peem and Manyoo are
the first pair to go in.

782
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:32,760
I believe Manyoo is capable.

783
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:37,440
We messed up in the first round
because everything moved so fast.

784
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:39,760
He felt it was too quick too.

785
00:38:39,840 --> 00:38:42,400
So when he failed the first round,
he panicked.

786
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:46,240
Go to the center mark.

787
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:47,960
And share the center.

788
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,520
You can't do it, Manyoo? It's okay.

789
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,080
I just jumped right in.

790
00:38:56,160 --> 00:38:58,600
I didn't hold my breath first.

791
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:01,240
As soon as I went under, I was like…

792
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:04,280
"I can't do this."
I had to come back up for air immediately.

793
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:07,280
Don't get too close.
You'll hit the edge of the frame.

794
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:09,080
Okay, get in when you're ready.

795
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:10,840
The clock is ticking.

796
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:15,400
I have a trauma from childhood.
I almost drowned in a pool with friends.

797
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:18,040
The panic is real.
I have to fight through it.

798
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:25,040
Okay, try to kiss.

799
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:26,960
See?

800
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,440
I'm quite disappointed in Manyoo and Peem.

801
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:33,440
Mainly because Manyoo couldn't stay under.

802
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:37,920
It was panic combined
with the pressure of the time limit.

803
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:41,000
He just could not stay underwater.

804
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:43,360
Can you do it? If not, let others go.

805
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:48,720
If I get through this,
I'll have pushed my limits further.

806
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:55,040
Take it slow with the kiss.

807
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:57,680
Face each other,
feel the moment, then kiss.

808
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,280
Don't actually blow bubbles.

809
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:01,960
It's a camera trick.
It's all about technique.

810
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:04,640
Go down. Slowly. Don't hide your…

811
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:06,160
Okay.

812
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:10,640
I could see it in his body.
I could see it in his eyes.

813
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:12,640
Even before he went under.

814
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:16,080
I gave him a chance,
but in the end, he just couldn't do it.

815
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:19,400
So I had him withdraw
and replaced him with someone else.

816
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:24,600
This is bad.
They gave us very little time.

817
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:27,000
After just a couple of takes,
this happens.

818
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:28,920
I'm definitely dragging the team down.

819
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:39,200
I was about seven years old.

820
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:40,120
Back then,

821
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:43,320
I went to the riverbank with some friends.

822
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,720
I didn't know how slippery it was.

823
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:49,920
I stepped on some clothes,
tripped, and fell into the river.

824
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:52,760
I struggled so hard.
I still remember it vividly.

825
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:56,120
As I struggled, it felt like I was dying.

826
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:05,640
Since then, I've been afraid of water.

827
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:09,160
Even at the beach, I won't go in.
I just watched.

828
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:13,440
Even now, it still does not feel safe.

829
00:41:13,520 --> 00:41:15,800
I'm still a bit anxious.

830
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:19,200
I'm not sure if I'll do well,
but I'll do my best.

831
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:26,280
I didn't expect much from Jacob and Leo.

832
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:28,080
I wanted to see them perform first

833
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:30,080
and see how they would adjust.

834
00:41:34,040 --> 00:41:36,320
Keep helping him.
Why are you pushing him upward?

835
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:39,480
When Mile was teaching,
he probably questioned if we'd make it.

836
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:42,560
Mile means well.
He wants what's best for the team.

837
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,720
I get it.

838
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:45,520
I understand.

839
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:47,760
I understand.

840
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:51,040
Leo is still panicking, but that's okay.

841
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:53,680
For this round, I'm satisfied with this.

842
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:06,840
You have to kiss. Give it a try.

843
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:11,560
If Mile says I have to kiss, I'll do it.

844
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:15,360
It's not about personal preference.
It's acting.

845
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:17,280
Just like Mile wants.

846
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:22,040
Actually, those two
had several interesting takes.

847
00:42:22,120 --> 00:42:23,760
They looked beautiful.

848
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:26,920
Seeing it underwater
gives us a better perspective.

849
00:42:27,480 --> 00:42:28,600
Ready?

850
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:30,160
- Very ready.
- Yes.

851
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:31,600
Ready?

852
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:33,360
The opening is key.

853
00:42:33,440 --> 00:42:37,200
I want to see a delicate touch.

854
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:40,000
Let's start with your stories.

855
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:43,600
What's your idea? Get up.

856
00:42:43,680 --> 00:42:45,840
I think he has what it takes.

857
00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:50,600
I want to give everyone a chance
to do what they've prepared.

858
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:54,440
Emotional connection is
about more than just a kiss.

859
00:42:54,520 --> 00:42:58,400
Eye contact, slow touches…

860
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,560
That has more intimacy.

861
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:01,960
I didn't give them too many instructions.

862
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:04,520
I want them to stay calm
long enough to try.

863
00:43:04,600 --> 00:43:07,280
Give it 30 seconds, then next.

864
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:08,920
Once I dive down,

865
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,920
I'll hold my partner while he floats.

866
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:14,520
Today, we're reviewing
the poses we planned.

867
00:43:14,600 --> 00:43:17,120
Ananda is reviewing everyone's ideas.

868
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:20,640
He's carefully checking each one.

869
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:24,320
If they can stay still,
we'll see their true potential.

870
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:26,120
- Tim is here.
- Hi.

871
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:27,520
Let me start.

872
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:30,920
Regarding the intimacy
and physical contact,

873
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:33,120
it doesn't have to be just a kiss, right?

874
00:43:33,200 --> 00:43:35,280
Can it be other types of touch?

875
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:36,440
Yes.

876
00:43:36,520 --> 00:43:38,040
It's like art, Ananda.

877
00:43:38,120 --> 00:43:42,360
As long as you both genuinely feel
the need to communicate that.

878
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:44,840
I think I understand Tim.

879
00:43:44,920 --> 00:43:48,440
Tim focuses on subtle emotions.

880
00:43:48,520 --> 00:43:49,720
What's the blocking?

881
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:51,200
This way.

882
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,720
Come on, hurry.

883
00:43:53,800 --> 00:43:57,840
This center gap
is the best angle for the camera.

884
00:43:57,920 --> 00:43:59,560
We have two, one wide, one tight.

885
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:01,280
And do we get more than one take?

886
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:03,080
Yes. You manage the time.

887
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,200
- Good luck!
- Thanks.

888
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:08,320
Okay. Go for it.

889
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:11,200
This is important.
Don't dive in and then look for your spot.

890
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:12,440
You won't see anything.

891
00:44:12,520 --> 00:44:15,320
Just relax.

892
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:18,320
Hold onto the edge.

893
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:19,880
I'm going down to watch.

894
00:44:20,640 --> 00:44:22,840
Time is short.

895
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:29,160
It's better to just relax
and get used to being underwater.

896
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:33,360
Kimhan looks the calmest.

897
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:35,440
I think he'll do well.

898
00:44:35,520 --> 00:44:37,480
Good. Keep it up.

899
00:44:38,480 --> 00:44:40,880
The key to this campaign

900
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:44,520
is holding your breath
for as long as possible.

901
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:45,520
Nine minutes left.

902
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:46,600
Got it.

903
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:48,000
Look at the frame.

904
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:50,040
That could help him.

905
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:52,760
It gave him some perspective.

906
00:44:52,840 --> 00:44:54,920
How's his movement?

907
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,120
What's the framing? How much is in shot?

908
00:44:57,200 --> 00:44:59,280
We need to focus on the physical contact.

909
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:02,800
The pose is fine,
but it's only a medium shot.

910
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:06,320
If you want a wider shot,
back away from the camera.

911
00:45:08,200 --> 00:45:11,760
Back on land, I had a lot of ideas.

912
00:45:11,840 --> 00:45:15,800
But when I actually tried it with PP,
I knew we had to change plans.

913
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:18,720
We have to keep it more contained.

914
00:45:20,680 --> 00:45:22,720
I can't swim.

915
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:26,320
I was so worried.
I didn't know what to do.

916
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,480
I was terrified I'd be a burden.

917
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:30,640
I tried diving in once during practice.

918
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:31,920
It was okay.

919
00:45:33,520 --> 00:45:35,800
I'm using goggles.

920
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:40,160
I want to see how long I can stay under.

921
00:45:47,240 --> 00:45:50,760
I think they just need to relax.

922
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:51,960
PP.

923
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:53,800
- Yes?
- Just go down.

924
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:55,960
Find the safety diver first.

925
00:45:56,040 --> 00:46:00,240
- Then get used to being underwater.
- One minute left.

926
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:01,960
Will this even work today?

927
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:05,320
Can I really take my goggles off?

928
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:06,560
Stuff like that.

929
00:46:06,640 --> 00:46:10,480
I took them off for a second,
then came right up. I panicked.

930
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:12,960
I was scared I couldn't stay underwater.

931
00:46:13,040 --> 00:46:15,360
I got stuck in a negative headspace.

932
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:17,120
I didn't know what to do.

933
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:19,680
The buoy! Hurry!

934
00:46:21,240 --> 00:46:22,360
Relax.

935
00:46:23,760 --> 00:46:25,960
Man, at that moment…

936
00:46:26,480 --> 00:46:28,760
I thought I couldn't do it.

937
00:46:28,840 --> 00:46:31,320
Everyone, we only have ten minutes.

938
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:32,680
Take a seat here.

939
00:46:32,760 --> 00:46:35,880
- Let's welcome Tim.
- Tim?

940
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:37,000
- Hello, Tim.
- Hi.

941
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:39,240
- Please, have a seat.
- Let's talk.

942
00:46:39,320 --> 00:46:41,520
First question.

943
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:43,480
What are the criteria?

944
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:44,960
Emotion is number one.

945
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:46,560
Follow the brief.

946
00:46:46,640 --> 00:46:48,600
But I'll add something extra.

947
00:46:48,680 --> 00:46:51,480
How do you decide between the two?

948
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:53,520
Who will be the winner?

949
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:55,800
Whoever performs better.

950
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:57,440
Whoever has the stronger delivery.

951
00:46:57,520 --> 00:46:59,760
Do they need to actually kiss?

952
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:05,000
If you can make us feel like
you're giving them the breath of life…

953
00:47:05,080 --> 00:47:06,640
That's the key.

954
00:47:06,720 --> 00:47:09,240
Acting, emotion, posing, whatever.

955
00:47:09,320 --> 00:47:10,680
Tim said emotion.

956
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:13,520
So focus on the desire.

957
00:47:13,600 --> 00:47:15,240
Rome, you're the rescuer first.

958
00:47:16,240 --> 00:47:17,840
Let's start the task.

959
00:47:17,920 --> 00:47:20,520
Three of you watch the monitor.

960
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:22,280
The other two, get in the water.

961
00:47:22,360 --> 00:47:24,320
Starting with Rome and Mew.

962
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:26,000
Relax. Breathe.

963
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:29,160
- Dive in.
- Three, two, one.

964
00:47:30,280 --> 00:47:31,160
Okay.

965
00:47:31,240 --> 00:47:33,120
Mew, go deeper if you can.

966
00:47:33,200 --> 00:47:36,880
Once we were underwater,
I knew Mew wasn't okay.

967
00:47:36,960 --> 00:47:41,800
- It was obvious. I'm rooting for him.
- I don't think he can go down.

968
00:47:41,880 --> 00:47:43,760
I'm only worried about Mew.

969
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:47,120
He could not sink
or dive down in either role.

970
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:49,240
He might be panicking.

971
00:47:49,880 --> 00:47:52,880
I was in the first pair,
but I couldn't sink.

972
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:57,680
So I asked for weights
to see if that would work.

973
00:47:57,760 --> 00:47:59,600
With weights, I was able to sink.

974
00:48:00,200 --> 00:48:01,440
But the pose was off.

975
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:03,560
Trust your partner. He'll help you.

976
00:48:04,520 --> 00:48:06,200
Easy, Mew. Easy.

977
00:48:07,200 --> 00:48:11,040
I think Rome did quite well.

978
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:13,560
Both as the victim and as the rescuer.

979
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:17,600
His build, his face, his hair…

980
00:48:17,680 --> 00:48:21,120
I thought his hair might cover his face.

981
00:48:21,200 --> 00:48:24,640
But in the end, Rome did a great job.

982
00:48:24,720 --> 00:48:27,000
Have you ever kissed anyone? Take it slow.

983
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:28,520
Like this.

984
00:48:28,600 --> 00:48:30,440
If he goes this way, you go that way.

985
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:34,160
Joong's direction and improv coaching
were excellent.

986
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:35,640
I'm really impressed.

987
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:37,480
Go. We still have time.

988
00:48:37,560 --> 00:48:41,640
I was so excited.
Off's time management was great.

989
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:43,000
Well done.

990
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:45,320
Good job. Just let go. He'll help you.

991
00:48:45,400 --> 00:48:48,640
Turn to the camera, kiss, then surface.

992
00:48:48,720 --> 00:48:51,240
Great job! Wow, that gave me chills.

993
00:48:51,840 --> 00:48:53,480
We actually kissed.

994
00:48:53,560 --> 00:48:55,520
I didn't think we would.

995
00:48:55,600 --> 00:48:57,960
It was just a lighting test.

996
00:48:58,800 --> 00:49:01,480
I tried to keep it real
to capture the right emotion.

997
00:49:01,560 --> 00:49:03,920
So it got a little intense.

998
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:06,320
Now it's Fox and Bonus.

999
00:49:06,400 --> 00:49:08,000
Joong, check the frame for them.

1000
00:49:08,080 --> 00:49:08,920
Okay.

1001
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:10,920
Good, good.

1002
00:49:11,560 --> 00:49:12,680
Got it?

1003
00:49:12,760 --> 00:49:14,640
How's the framing, Joong? Too high?

1004
00:49:14,720 --> 00:49:17,000
A bit. They need to go lower.

1005
00:49:17,080 --> 00:49:19,320
I think this is enough practice.

1006
00:49:19,400 --> 00:49:21,960
I've been in the water
and was holding my breath.

1007
00:49:22,040 --> 00:49:23,760
I was testing how long I could last.

1008
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:25,680
Seeing what poses I can pull off.

1009
00:49:25,760 --> 00:49:27,440
Checking myself on camera.

1010
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:31,160
Don't overact.
It's exhausting if you do too much.

1011
00:49:31,240 --> 00:49:32,400
I had to save my breath.

1012
00:49:32,480 --> 00:49:34,480
Fox and Bonus are doing great.

1013
00:49:34,560 --> 00:49:39,080
I feel like Bonus could be
our biggest hope in this episode.

1014
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:49,840
Welcome back to "The Spirit of Unity."

1015
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:54,880
Today, our judge will focus
on physical communication,

1016
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:58,720
teamwork, and the power
of trust underwater.

1017
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:01,680
But before we begin today's competition,

1018
00:50:01,760 --> 00:50:05,600
I'd like to introduce another key judge
for this master class.

1019
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:08,000
A multi-talented, iconic artist

1020
00:50:08,080 --> 00:50:11,120
who shines in every role he takes on.

1021
00:50:11,200 --> 00:50:14,120
Please give a big round of applause
for PP Krit!

1022
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:18,760
- Hello.
- Hello.

1023
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:22,440
PP KRIT, ICONIC THAI ARTIST AND ACTOR

1024
00:50:22,520 --> 00:50:24,760
- Hello, Ananda.
- Hello.

1025
00:50:25,320 --> 00:50:27,680
- You've already locked your target.
- I'm nervous now.

1026
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:33,640
PP, my team consists of Mew, Pom,
Fox, Bonus, and Rome.

1027
00:50:33,720 --> 00:50:36,160
- The ones ready to be eliminated.
- Hey!

1028
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:38,840
- Please look after them.
- Will do.

1029
00:50:38,920 --> 00:50:42,720
I already know PP Krit well.

1030
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:45,560
I'm glad he's here. It helps us relax.

1031
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:47,720
All right, if everyone is ready,

1032
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:51,080
let's begin "The Spirit of Unity."

1033
00:50:51,160 --> 00:50:52,800
Please welcome our first pair,

1034
00:50:52,880 --> 00:50:54,000
Peem and Mew!

1035
00:50:54,880 --> 00:50:56,640
- Let's go.
- Come on!

1036
00:50:57,680 --> 00:51:00,840
The one we fear most is Mentor Off's team.

1037
00:51:00,920 --> 00:51:02,480
Peem is one of the frontrunners.

1038
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,960
Ready? Start the clock!

1039
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:07,520
Do the original plan first.

1040
00:51:07,600 --> 00:51:09,360
- Then try again for me.
- Got it.

1041
00:51:09,440 --> 00:51:12,160
Do what we prepared first.
I want to show them.

1042
00:51:12,240 --> 00:51:15,840
Just keep one thing in mind…

1043
00:51:17,880 --> 00:51:19,120
Stay calm. Take it slow.

1044
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:22,280
I need to feel the emotion.

1045
00:51:25,760 --> 00:51:27,880
Wait for "action." Stay calm.

1046
00:51:27,960 --> 00:51:29,480
- Beautiful. Good.
- Action!

1047
00:51:30,200 --> 00:51:31,440
Good.

1048
00:51:32,200 --> 00:51:34,040
Good. Okay.

1049
00:51:34,120 --> 00:51:35,360
Kill it!

1050
00:51:36,040 --> 00:51:38,800
- Okay, great frame.
- Turn, turn!

1051
00:51:38,880 --> 00:51:39,720
Well done.

1052
00:51:39,800 --> 00:51:40,840
Mew surprised me.

1053
00:51:40,920 --> 00:51:45,160
During practice, he didn't do very well.

1054
00:51:45,240 --> 00:51:48,840
I wasn't sure.
Honestly, underwater, you're lost.

1055
00:51:48,920 --> 00:51:50,080
I can't see anything.

1056
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:51,400
Four minutes left.

1057
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:54,120
Can you both try option two?

1058
00:51:54,200 --> 00:51:55,800
Four minutes left. We can do it.

1059
00:51:55,880 --> 00:51:56,800
Are you okay?

1060
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,160
Switch. Go down.

1061
00:51:58,240 --> 00:51:59,400
- Want to switch?
- Sure.

1062
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:01,880
- You want me to sink? Okay, I'll sink.
- Okay.

1063
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:04,480
This was Mentor Mile's idea.

1064
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:08,600
I was supposed to pretend to be drowning

1065
00:52:08,680 --> 00:52:10,640
so the other person could swim to me.

1066
00:52:10,720 --> 00:52:12,480
- Go, Mew!
- Don't turn your back.

1067
00:52:12,560 --> 00:52:14,440
- Good, beautiful.
- Just like that.

1068
00:52:14,520 --> 00:52:15,760
- Kiss!
- Beautiful.

1069
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:16,960
They need to slow down.

1070
00:52:17,040 --> 00:52:19,000
- It's becoming…
- Too rushed.

1071
00:52:19,080 --> 00:52:20,800
It's like they're rushing to kiss.

1072
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:23,080
Scrambling to kiss, like,
"Where's your mouth?"

1073
00:52:23,720 --> 00:52:24,640
"I'm right here!"

1074
00:52:24,720 --> 00:52:26,160
Turn the other way and kiss.

1075
00:52:26,240 --> 00:52:27,800
The other way. Just like that.

1076
00:52:27,880 --> 00:52:29,200
Tease it a bit.

1077
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:31,040
The way we came up was beautiful.

1078
00:52:31,120 --> 00:52:32,200
Felt like a mermaid.

1079
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:33,120
Not good?

1080
00:52:33,200 --> 00:52:36,200
It's too fast. They rushed.
They won't listen either.

1081
00:52:36,960 --> 00:52:40,440
I tell them to stay calm,
and they just dive in.

1082
00:52:40,520 --> 00:52:41,360
Well…

1083
00:52:42,120 --> 00:52:43,280
It's a shame.

1084
00:52:43,360 --> 00:52:45,480
Okay, this time, take it slow.

1085
00:52:45,560 --> 00:52:47,040
Focus. Ready? Go.

1086
00:52:51,520 --> 00:52:54,400
It's okay, Peem. Calm down.

1087
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:55,800
Option two didn't work.

1088
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:58,480
So we're going back to option one.

1089
00:52:58,560 --> 00:53:00,480
Only three minutes left.

1090
00:53:00,560 --> 00:53:01,640
Time's almost up.

1091
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:03,760
Take it slow.

1092
00:53:03,840 --> 00:53:05,240
Feel it. Use your feelings.

1093
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:08,000
- Eye contact. Feel it.
- Emotion. Sharing a breath.

1094
00:53:08,080 --> 00:53:09,560
Slowly bring him up.

1095
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:10,640
Oh, that's good.

1096
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:12,280
This is nerve-wracking.

1097
00:53:12,360 --> 00:53:14,520
- Watching men kiss…
- It's intense.

1098
00:53:14,600 --> 00:53:15,720
This was the best take.

1099
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:19,640
I think the judges will like
this take too.

1100
00:53:19,720 --> 00:53:20,720
One minute left.

1101
00:53:20,800 --> 00:53:22,400
If you can do it in one minute, go.

1102
00:53:22,480 --> 00:53:24,600
Do you want to?
If you do, get in there now.

1103
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:26,760
The crew said
one minute for the last shot.

1104
00:53:26,840 --> 00:53:28,080
Okay, I'm going in.

1105
00:53:28,160 --> 00:53:29,320
Mile.

1106
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:30,480
He's the real deal.

1107
00:53:30,560 --> 00:53:34,400
I just imagined that he was my lover
and that he was there to help me.

1108
00:53:34,480 --> 00:53:37,000
Look at each other. Pull back. I love you.

1109
00:53:37,080 --> 00:53:38,560
I want you to make love.

1110
00:53:38,640 --> 00:53:40,240
Go. More intense foreplay.

1111
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:43,000
I don't know, but I gave it my all.

1112
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:45,440
I'm starting to feel it now.

1113
00:53:45,520 --> 00:53:47,080
Go. Take it to the surface. Go.

1114
00:53:49,280 --> 00:53:51,480
I really hate what you said.

1115
00:53:51,560 --> 00:53:54,640
When Mew and Peem worked together,
their chemistry was undeniable.

1116
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:56,480
You could see their dedication.

1117
00:53:56,560 --> 00:53:58,760
It exceeded my expectations by a lot.

1118
00:53:58,840 --> 00:54:01,840
Moving on to the second pair,
Kimhan and Pom.

1119
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:04,480
The plan was one of us is drowning,
the other rescues him

1120
00:54:04,560 --> 00:54:07,520
and gives him the "breath of life."
That's the concept.

1121
00:54:07,600 --> 00:54:08,800
Are they holding hands?

1122
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:09,800
That's cute.

1123
00:54:09,880 --> 00:54:13,400
It's a way for them to sync up
before they start performing.

1124
00:54:13,480 --> 00:54:15,240
Go. Start the clock.

1125
00:54:15,320 --> 00:54:17,160
Okay, you guys take the lead.

1126
00:54:17,240 --> 00:54:19,320
Relax and show us
what you've prepared first.

1127
00:54:19,400 --> 00:54:22,040
Who's going down to…

1128
00:54:22,120 --> 00:54:23,360
- Kimhan starts.
- I will.

1129
00:54:23,440 --> 00:54:24,560
I'm really nervous.

1130
00:54:24,640 --> 00:54:26,680
I'm afraid he's trying too hard.

1131
00:54:26,760 --> 00:54:28,720
He can manage his own thoughts,

1132
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:30,720
but he can't control others.

1133
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:33,000
Kim, relax. Take it slow.

1134
00:54:33,080 --> 00:54:33,920
Take it easy.

1135
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:36,720
Pom, just like we practiced.
Is the positioning okay, Off?

1136
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:38,200
Wait for the actors.

1137
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:42,400
My method is to use eye contact
to feel each other's emotions.

1138
00:54:50,200 --> 00:54:51,480
Beautiful, Pom.

1139
00:54:52,200 --> 00:54:53,280
Beautiful.

1140
00:54:53,360 --> 00:54:56,320
The plan was to go down
and wake the other.

1141
00:54:56,400 --> 00:54:58,400
But after that, it was all improvised.

1142
00:54:58,480 --> 00:54:59,400
Watch the angle.

1143
00:55:02,280 --> 00:55:04,280
They were actually flirting.

1144
00:55:04,360 --> 00:55:07,360
The emotions were felt,
and the chemistry showed.

1145
00:55:07,440 --> 00:55:08,280
It was perfect.

1146
00:55:08,360 --> 00:55:10,400
Great. I love it.

1147
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:12,280
Mentor Mile, is your heart racing?

1148
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:14,440
Definitely. Very fast.

1149
00:55:14,520 --> 00:55:17,360
Pom has been a dark horse
since the runway challenge.

1150
00:55:17,440 --> 00:55:19,320
Wow, he's actually terrifying.

1151
00:55:21,600 --> 00:55:25,120
Good. Watch your arms.
Don't block each other.

1152
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:26,520
Nice.

1153
00:55:26,600 --> 00:55:31,080
Kim and Pom had a beginning,
middle, and end.

1154
00:55:31,160 --> 00:55:33,400
They hit the time limit
and stuck the ending.

1155
00:55:34,480 --> 00:55:35,480
I'm screwed.

1156
00:55:37,040 --> 00:55:39,360
Are you a mermaid?
You've been underwater too long.

1157
00:55:39,440 --> 00:55:40,560
That's it.

1158
00:55:42,520 --> 00:55:45,360
So good. Kimhan and Pom were amazing.

1159
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:47,720
Their chemistry today was off the charts.

1160
00:55:47,800 --> 00:55:49,920
I can't keep my face cool. So intense.

1161
00:55:50,000 --> 00:55:52,520
I liked everything.
Your choreography was beautiful.

1162
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:55,520
But this time,
I want more variation in your pacing.

1163
00:55:55,600 --> 00:55:56,960
Underwater, it feels rushed.

1164
00:55:57,040 --> 00:55:59,160
It was shaky at first
because it was too fast.

1165
00:55:59,240 --> 00:56:02,160
So we changed our strategy
and switched positions.

1166
00:56:02,240 --> 00:56:03,400
Now I'll rescue him.

1167
00:56:04,600 --> 00:56:06,520
Beautiful.

1168
00:56:06,600 --> 00:56:07,920
- Beautiful.
- Great pose.

1169
00:56:11,880 --> 00:56:12,720
Oh my God!

1170
00:56:12,800 --> 00:56:14,280
I'm shocked.

1171
00:56:14,360 --> 00:56:17,080
That looked like
a lot more than just a rescue.

1172
00:56:17,160 --> 00:56:18,440
When I went under…

1173
00:56:18,520 --> 00:56:21,400
I felt my character
gravitating toward him.

1174
00:56:21,480 --> 00:56:23,280
I'd want to be with him, would I not?

1175
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:26,680
Kim got the timing right.
He went all the way down.

1176
00:56:26,760 --> 00:56:28,320
When Pom started to float away,

1177
00:56:28,400 --> 00:56:31,000
he pulled him back into position.
It was romantic.

1178
00:56:31,080 --> 00:56:32,800
It was great. Well done.

1179
00:56:32,880 --> 00:56:35,360
- So beautiful.
- Stay in character.

1180
00:56:35,440 --> 00:56:37,160
These two really connect.

1181
00:56:37,240 --> 00:56:38,960
Their chemistry is great to me.

1182
00:56:39,040 --> 00:56:42,320
They give and take
from each other perfectly.

1183
00:56:42,400 --> 00:56:44,000
Regardless of their positions,

1184
00:56:44,080 --> 00:56:46,600
they both handled their roles well.

1185
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:48,640
Four minutes left.

1186
00:56:48,720 --> 00:56:50,680
That was excellent. When you push off…

1187
00:56:50,760 --> 00:56:52,160
The eye contact is good.

1188
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:53,720
Push off slowly, Pom.

1189
00:56:53,800 --> 00:56:55,040
Go down when you're ready.

1190
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:57,000
They're under.

1191
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:59,880
Pull him back. Hold. Lock eyes.

1192
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:01,000
Our lips touched,

1193
00:57:01,080 --> 00:57:05,080
but we were weightless,
just flowing with the mood.

1194
00:57:05,160 --> 00:57:07,160
Just flowing with our improvisation.

1195
00:57:07,240 --> 00:57:09,080
I think he stayed in the moment well.

1196
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:11,440
That's vital for acting.

1197
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:14,160
One more would be great.

1198
00:57:14,240 --> 00:57:16,040
- Switch places?
- How much time is left?

1199
00:57:16,120 --> 00:57:17,120
Final 30 seconds.

1200
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:18,240
Already?

1201
00:57:18,320 --> 00:57:19,640
Okay, let's try.

1202
00:57:19,720 --> 00:57:23,080
In the final 30 seconds,
I felt like we had the experience.

1203
00:57:23,160 --> 00:57:24,080
Twenty seconds left.

1204
00:57:27,160 --> 00:57:28,920
Beautiful.

1205
00:57:29,000 --> 00:57:31,120
Kimhan has a tactic for this game.

1206
00:57:31,200 --> 00:57:35,640
He's an actor who knows
how to pressure his partner.

1207
00:57:35,720 --> 00:57:37,680
He used that to his advantage.

1208
00:57:39,760 --> 00:57:40,880
- Nice.
- Five.

1209
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:45,400
- Come up.
- Four, three, two, one. Time's up.

1210
00:57:47,120 --> 00:57:48,720
It felt right, so we came back up.

1211
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:49,640
That's it!

1212
00:57:50,600 --> 00:57:52,320
Great job.

1213
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:55,880
I made the right choice picking Kimhan.
It has to be Pom-Kimhan, right?

1214
00:57:56,960 --> 00:57:58,360
Let's take turns.

1215
00:57:58,440 --> 00:57:59,880
Kimhan-Pom, Pom-Kimhan.

1216
00:57:59,960 --> 00:58:01,360
What do you guys think?

1217
00:58:01,440 --> 00:58:03,160
Let's move on to the third pair.

1218
00:58:04,920 --> 00:58:06,960
Ready? Start the clock.

1219
00:58:17,320 --> 00:58:19,680
I just want this pair
to have some work to show.

1220
00:58:19,760 --> 00:58:22,120
If Leo fails, Lincoln fails too.

1221
00:58:32,160 --> 00:58:34,400
It's hard. If I find it hard,

1222
00:58:34,480 --> 00:58:36,120
what will Leo do?

1223
00:58:36,200 --> 00:58:37,720
Only seven minutes left.

1224
00:58:38,360 --> 00:58:40,360
For me, it comes down to their practice.

1225
00:58:40,440 --> 00:58:41,680
For one take,

1226
00:58:41,760 --> 00:58:45,120
we need to see how long
we can hold our breath.

1227
00:58:45,200 --> 00:58:48,760
Lincoln and Leo.
This pair is taking forever to get in.

1228
00:58:48,840 --> 00:58:51,480
- Leo seems to have childhood trauma.
- Oh, really?

1229
00:58:51,560 --> 00:58:55,720
He almost drowned and has been
terrified of water ever since.

1230
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:58,960
He has to face his fear to be The Face.

1231
00:59:07,440 --> 00:59:09,760
I'll let you direct.

1232
00:59:09,840 --> 00:59:13,520
I'll handle Leo.

1233
00:59:13,600 --> 00:59:14,640
Okay.

1234
00:59:14,720 --> 00:59:15,840
Let's just focus on

1235
00:59:15,920 --> 00:59:18,280
- getting one take first.
- We can add more later.

1236
00:59:18,360 --> 00:59:20,200
Lincoln wasn't okay with the kiss.

1237
00:59:20,280 --> 00:59:22,960
So I had him focus on graceful swimming.

1238
00:59:23,040 --> 00:59:24,640
To keep the movements artistic.

1239
00:59:24,720 --> 00:59:26,160
Leo, can you hear me?

1240
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:39,080
Five minutes in and not a single take.

1241
00:59:47,680 --> 00:59:48,600
Beautiful.

1242
00:59:52,920 --> 00:59:57,520
Leo has low energy,
but a natural calmness.

1243
00:59:57,600 --> 00:59:58,840
Even when he's scared.

1244
00:59:59,400 --> 01:00:00,680
Only three minutes left.

1245
01:00:00,760 --> 01:00:02,000
Come up!

1246
01:00:04,920 --> 01:00:07,320
What's next?

1247
01:00:07,400 --> 01:00:08,720
We're done.

1248
01:00:09,800 --> 01:00:12,640
To me, they were both quite flat.

1249
01:00:12,720 --> 01:00:14,480
Lincoln's delivery was weak.

1250
01:00:15,080 --> 01:00:18,040
If Leo's panicking,
he needs to be more intense.

1251
01:00:18,120 --> 01:00:19,680
He needs to make Leo feel more.

1252
01:00:19,760 --> 01:00:22,440
Well, they got a take. Can't complain.

1253
01:00:22,520 --> 01:00:24,280
Mentor Off is stressed now.

1254
01:00:25,160 --> 01:00:26,600
Are you stressed, Off?

1255
01:00:26,680 --> 01:00:29,480
So stressed.
This show is giving me gray hair.

1256
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:30,560
- Really?
- Yeah.

1257
01:00:30,640 --> 01:00:32,040
How many minutes are left?

1258
01:00:32,120 --> 01:00:33,680
One minute and 30 seconds.

1259
01:00:37,640 --> 01:00:38,480
Here they are.

1260
01:00:51,240 --> 01:00:53,360
They want to see emotion.
No need for a story.

1261
01:00:53,440 --> 01:00:54,960
We can make this a special cut.

1262
01:00:55,040 --> 01:00:56,840
What engages people

1263
01:00:56,920 --> 01:00:58,960
isn't just the perfect kiss.

1264
01:00:59,040 --> 01:01:00,320
It's the journey.

1265
01:01:01,640 --> 01:01:03,000
Only 30 seconds.

1266
01:01:05,040 --> 01:01:06,360
Okay, we got some moments.

1267
01:01:06,440 --> 01:01:09,200
Not really wowing. Nothing stands out.

1268
01:01:09,280 --> 01:01:12,480
I like that the other mentors
manage their time this way.

1269
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:13,560
Makes it easy for us.

1270
01:01:13,640 --> 01:01:15,600
I told them to stick to the plan.

1271
01:01:15,680 --> 01:01:18,120
His performance might not win first place.

1272
01:01:18,200 --> 01:01:20,640
That's okay.
He did really well in his own way.

1273
01:01:20,720 --> 01:01:23,760
Leo deserves
a lot of credit for his bravery.

1274
01:01:23,840 --> 01:01:26,600
He is afraid of water,
but he still pulled it off.

1275
01:01:26,680 --> 01:01:28,400
- He fought for his life.
- Exactly.

1276
01:01:29,080 --> 01:01:30,920
He might not have done many takes.

1277
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:33,400
But the ones he did, he gave it his all.

1278
01:01:33,480 --> 01:01:35,000
I think everyone can see that.

1279
01:01:35,080 --> 01:01:36,400
On to the fourth pair.

1280
01:01:36,480 --> 01:01:37,840
Fox and Manyoo.

1281
01:01:37,920 --> 01:01:39,200
So cool.

1282
01:01:39,280 --> 01:01:40,280
I'm paired with Fox.

1283
01:01:40,360 --> 01:01:43,800
Ten minutes go by so fast
for an underwater campaign.

1284
01:01:43,880 --> 01:01:45,720
Okay, if everyone's ready.

1285
01:01:45,800 --> 01:01:47,240
- Start the clock.
- Right away.

1286
01:01:47,320 --> 01:01:48,560
Go with what you want.

1287
01:01:49,080 --> 01:01:51,080
- Take it slow.
- Got anything to show us?

1288
01:01:51,160 --> 01:01:52,360
This monitor is dead.

1289
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:55,240
Should we take a break?
This team gets extra time for nothing.

1290
01:01:55,320 --> 01:01:57,640
Hey, I'm already counting.
One minute down.

1291
01:01:57,720 --> 01:02:00,360
Cut! Please separate the mentors
from the contestants.

1292
01:02:00,440 --> 01:02:01,600
Cut for now.

1293
01:02:01,680 --> 01:02:03,360
- Come on out.
- Technical issue.

1294
01:02:03,440 --> 01:02:04,280
Yeah.

1295
01:02:04,360 --> 01:02:05,760
What did I do wrong?

1296
01:02:05,840 --> 01:02:07,400
Technical issue. Sorry about that.

1297
01:02:07,480 --> 01:02:09,400
It's normal,
but it shouldn't happen often.

1298
01:02:09,480 --> 01:02:10,840
Mentors, please.

1299
01:02:14,440 --> 01:02:16,640
Take it slow.

1300
01:02:16,720 --> 01:02:18,040
I'm acting like it's a drama.

1301
01:02:18,120 --> 01:02:20,680
The vibe of two friends
who like each other.

1302
01:02:24,800 --> 01:02:26,280
I was suffocating, I tell you.

1303
01:02:26,360 --> 01:02:28,520
Just kissing like that.

1304
01:02:30,880 --> 01:02:31,720
What was that?

1305
01:02:32,240 --> 01:02:33,440
What's the goal here?

1306
01:02:33,520 --> 01:02:36,800
- I can't see anything.
- Can you start from underwater?

1307
01:02:36,880 --> 01:02:38,400
Let's go again. Keep it together.

1308
01:02:41,840 --> 01:02:43,480
It's my first time kissing a guy.

1309
01:02:43,560 --> 01:02:46,320
It feels like a whole new experience.

1310
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:47,600
Eight minutes left.

1311
01:02:47,680 --> 01:02:49,440
Take it slow.

1312
01:02:49,520 --> 01:02:51,600
Fox, Manyoo. No, this isn't working.

1313
01:02:51,680 --> 01:02:52,600
Hold it.

1314
01:02:55,000 --> 01:02:57,080
- I can't do this.
- It looks too forced.

1315
01:02:57,160 --> 01:02:58,840
"My mouth is here. Where's yours?"

1316
01:02:58,920 --> 01:03:01,040
And they hit the surface in a second.

1317
01:03:04,520 --> 01:03:05,800
Crap.

1318
01:03:05,880 --> 01:03:10,600
Fox goes underwater for barely
five seconds and comes right back up.

1319
01:03:10,680 --> 01:03:12,160
Not sure what to add to that.

1320
01:03:12,240 --> 01:03:15,200
Do you want to change the story?
Want to do something else?

1321
01:03:15,280 --> 01:03:16,360
I can go and help him.

1322
01:03:16,440 --> 01:03:17,520
- Yeah.
- Okay.

1323
01:03:18,520 --> 01:03:20,840
And the movements aren't pretty at all.

1324
01:03:20,920 --> 01:03:23,640
They just drop down
and nibble each other going up.

1325
01:03:23,720 --> 01:03:25,840
Do a spin. Spin around a bit.

1326
01:03:25,920 --> 01:03:27,600
Then they reach the surface.

1327
01:03:28,240 --> 01:03:29,640
Quick, quick!

1328
01:03:29,720 --> 01:03:31,360
Just act. No need to rush.

1329
01:03:31,440 --> 01:03:33,960
Okay, that was good. Use this storyline.

1330
01:03:34,040 --> 01:03:34,880
Go.

1331
01:03:35,880 --> 01:03:38,280
The energy was okay at first.

1332
01:03:38,360 --> 01:03:39,960
But during the later takes…

1333
01:03:40,880 --> 01:03:42,000
What happened?

1334
01:03:43,520 --> 01:03:44,800
No. Come up. Again.

1335
01:03:44,880 --> 01:03:45,960
He's frustrated.

1336
01:03:46,040 --> 01:03:50,560
I felt like he tried to help,
but it's like he stopped responding.

1337
01:03:50,640 --> 01:03:53,640
He just spun when I told him to.
He didn't get it.

1338
01:03:53,720 --> 01:03:55,720
It was a mess. I have to admit that.

1339
01:03:55,800 --> 01:03:58,080
Fox, you can go down and get ready first.

1340
01:03:58,160 --> 01:04:00,440
Manyoo, that's good.
But just take it slow.

1341
01:04:00,520 --> 01:04:03,520
It's still weird
because it doesn't feel natural.

1342
01:04:03,600 --> 01:04:04,800
We're not used to it.

1343
01:04:04,880 --> 01:04:06,480
Three minutes left.

1344
01:04:06,560 --> 01:04:07,920
Plenty of time. Don't worry.

1345
01:04:08,000 --> 01:04:09,920
Go. Manyoo, calm down.

1346
01:04:10,000 --> 01:04:11,000
Fox, are you okay?

1347
01:04:12,120 --> 01:04:13,120
Swim.

1348
01:04:13,200 --> 01:04:15,720
He put on a snorkel and went underwater…

1349
01:04:15,800 --> 01:04:17,440
But then he came up. Why?

1350
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:19,480
- The vibe is not there.
- No.

1351
01:04:19,560 --> 01:04:22,680
Stick to what you can do.
Like what we did at first.

1352
01:04:22,760 --> 01:04:24,800
Why was he doing this?

1353
01:04:24,880 --> 01:04:26,800
No one understood what he was doing.

1354
01:04:26,880 --> 01:04:29,080
- Don't feel pressured.
- Spin slowly.

1355
01:04:29,160 --> 01:04:30,480
When you're ready.

1356
01:04:30,560 --> 01:04:31,800
Off, give me a sec.

1357
01:04:31,880 --> 01:04:35,840
Manyoo, take it slow. You can kiss.
Take your time kissing and deciding.

1358
01:04:35,920 --> 01:04:36,880
But make it clear.

1359
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:38,880
I feel invisible.

1360
01:04:38,960 --> 01:04:42,600
Trying to stay quiet and out of the way.

1361
01:04:42,680 --> 01:04:46,400
I could only look at Tim and PP
with pitiful eyes.

1362
01:04:46,480 --> 01:04:48,960
One minute and 45 seconds left.

1363
01:04:49,040 --> 01:04:50,600
You have 15 seconds to breathe.

1364
01:04:50,680 --> 01:04:53,160
Then go down there for a minute
and show me something.

1365
01:04:53,240 --> 01:04:55,240
If you can't do it, tell me.

1366
01:04:55,320 --> 01:04:58,480
Tell me what you need.
I've taught you everything.

1367
01:04:58,560 --> 01:05:02,280
Is this all you've got? On Fox's end.

1368
01:05:02,360 --> 01:05:04,840
You need a motive. Be more detailed, like…

1369
01:05:04,920 --> 01:05:08,640
You don't have to act like
"Oh my God, I love you" right away.

1370
01:05:09,280 --> 01:05:10,520
Look, Manyoo.

1371
01:05:10,600 --> 01:05:13,240
If you think you can do better, go down.

1372
01:05:13,320 --> 01:05:15,840
Fox, take it slow. It's the last take.

1373
01:05:15,920 --> 01:05:16,760
It's a shame.

1374
01:05:16,840 --> 01:05:20,320
Honestly, his partner dragged him down.
I don't know what to do.

1375
01:05:20,400 --> 01:05:23,120
It's not just one person acting like this.

1376
01:05:23,200 --> 01:05:25,960
It's both of them.
We couldn't capture anything.

1377
01:05:26,040 --> 01:05:27,320
Last minute.

1378
01:05:27,400 --> 01:05:29,040
- You have to go down.
- Deeper.

1379
01:05:29,120 --> 01:05:30,600
Find your camera angle.

1380
01:05:30,680 --> 01:05:31,880
Hold his face.

1381
01:05:33,440 --> 01:05:34,560
Kiss.

1382
01:05:34,640 --> 01:05:36,040
Good job. Watch the angle.

1383
01:05:36,120 --> 01:05:37,560
Yes. Turn to the camera.

1384
01:05:38,920 --> 01:05:40,280
Okay.

1385
01:05:40,360 --> 01:05:43,160
No panic at all.
He did whatever I told him.

1386
01:05:43,240 --> 01:05:46,120
I'm just glad he could do it.

1387
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:48,080
At least I survived this.

1388
01:05:50,200 --> 01:05:51,600
That works. It's good.

1389
01:05:51,680 --> 01:05:52,960
- Twenty-five seconds.
- Go.

1390
01:05:53,600 --> 01:05:55,240
- One, two.
- Go for it.

1391
01:05:57,400 --> 01:05:58,840
Beautiful.

1392
01:05:58,920 --> 01:06:00,720
Beautiful.

1393
01:06:01,400 --> 01:06:02,680
They need more movements.

1394
01:06:02,760 --> 01:06:03,760
Not enough dynamics.

1395
01:06:03,840 --> 01:06:07,680
I understand him, but I stayed quiet
so he'd keep trying on his own.

1396
01:06:07,760 --> 01:06:10,440
I don't know if the result will be good,

1397
01:06:10,520 --> 01:06:13,440
but between dying in the water
and dying in the Black Room,

1398
01:06:13,520 --> 01:06:15,760
I'd rather die in the water.

1399
01:06:15,840 --> 01:06:16,800
- Time's up.
- Okay.

1400
01:06:18,040 --> 01:06:19,120
Great.

1401
01:06:19,200 --> 01:06:21,800
He improved.
He tried hard. Fox tried hard.

1402
01:06:21,880 --> 01:06:23,800
But maybe not hard enough.

1403
01:06:28,920 --> 01:06:30,560
We're halfway through.

1404
01:06:30,640 --> 01:06:33,520
Next pair, please. Donut and Bonus.

1405
01:06:33,600 --> 01:06:35,280
They're both cool guys.

1406
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:37,120
I didn't expect them to pair up

1407
01:06:37,200 --> 01:06:39,840
and kiss underwater like this.

1408
01:06:39,920 --> 01:06:41,200
Hey, we gave you a new name.

1409
01:06:41,280 --> 01:06:42,160
Dobo.

1410
01:06:42,240 --> 01:06:44,280
- Is everyone ready? Come on in.
- Let's go.

1411
01:06:44,360 --> 01:06:45,560
- Let's go.
- Let's get it.

1412
01:06:45,640 --> 01:06:46,760
The favorites.

1413
01:06:46,840 --> 01:06:49,000
I love them. I love Dobo.

1414
01:06:49,080 --> 01:06:51,280
There's chemistry already.

1415
01:06:51,360 --> 01:06:54,560
- This pair is interesting.
- Very interesting.

1416
01:06:54,640 --> 01:06:57,800
This pair looks quite different
from the rest.

1417
01:06:57,880 --> 01:07:00,640
Very masculine, kind of a bad-boy vibe.

1418
01:07:00,720 --> 01:07:01,560
Dobo.

1419
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:03,120
Bring it on, Dobo.

1420
01:07:03,200 --> 01:07:04,800
Relax.

1421
01:07:04,880 --> 01:07:07,440
Do, if you're ready, tell Bo.

1422
01:07:07,520 --> 01:07:09,880
Let me know if I'm not in the center.

1423
01:07:09,960 --> 01:07:13,280
It's fine. Let's do one take first,
then I'll adjust you.

1424
01:07:13,360 --> 01:07:14,280
Team Dobo.

1425
01:07:14,360 --> 01:07:16,160
Young gang vibe.

1426
01:07:16,240 --> 01:07:18,320
It was unexpected,
and they fully committed.

1427
01:07:21,960 --> 01:07:23,280
Wow.

1428
01:07:23,360 --> 01:07:27,160
They went down, and Bonus
dove beautifully from the edge.

1429
01:07:27,240 --> 01:07:28,520
So beautiful.

1430
01:07:28,600 --> 01:07:30,400
Great job. Beautiful.

1431
01:07:30,480 --> 01:07:31,320
Beautiful.

1432
01:07:31,400 --> 01:07:34,800
They did their roles well.
Donut went down first.

1433
01:07:34,880 --> 01:07:36,960
- Watch the camera angle.
- Good.

1434
01:07:37,040 --> 01:07:38,960
Chills. You gave us chills.

1435
01:07:39,040 --> 01:07:40,680
That dive.

1436
01:07:40,760 --> 01:07:43,040
No other pair did that.

1437
01:07:43,120 --> 01:07:44,920
The underwater spin.

1438
01:07:45,800 --> 01:07:47,920
It's the rugged chemistry I wanted.

1439
01:07:48,000 --> 01:07:50,440
Yeah, something new.

1440
01:07:50,520 --> 01:07:52,760
They're the first pair to do this.
It's refreshing.

1441
01:07:53,840 --> 01:07:54,840
Are you okay?

1442
01:07:54,920 --> 01:07:56,160
That was okay.

1443
01:07:56,240 --> 01:07:57,720
Relax. Slow down.

1444
01:07:57,800 --> 01:08:02,320
Donut was another one I worried about.
Because he panicked earlier.

1445
01:08:02,400 --> 01:08:05,720
He had the spirit.
Did you see his face when he came up?

1446
01:08:07,880 --> 01:08:11,160
I love what they choreographed.

1447
01:08:11,240 --> 01:08:14,360
I love their fighting spirit.

1448
01:08:14,440 --> 01:08:16,439
Slowly. Breathe slowly.

1449
01:08:16,520 --> 01:08:18,279
- You guys like it?
- Yes, no problem.

1450
01:08:18,359 --> 01:08:19,880
Do we stop once we surface?

1451
01:08:19,960 --> 01:08:22,279
Don't break character until you go up.

1452
01:08:22,359 --> 01:08:23,840
Seven minutes left.

1453
01:08:27,479 --> 01:08:29,040
Where is this spirit coming from?

1454
01:08:29,120 --> 01:08:31,600
Who are they channeling?
Where's this energy from?

1455
01:08:31,680 --> 01:08:33,479
They're different people underwater.

1456
01:08:34,840 --> 01:08:36,000
Slowly. Relax.

1457
01:08:36,080 --> 01:08:38,120
Slowly. Relax.

1458
01:08:38,200 --> 01:08:39,920
Eye contact. Look at each other.

1459
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:42,080
Take your time. Slowly.

1460
01:08:45,080 --> 01:08:46,000
Okay.

1461
01:08:48,960 --> 01:08:50,920
They even gave us extra gasps.

1462
01:08:51,000 --> 01:08:54,560
Are you sure about this?
Catch your breath first.

1463
01:08:54,640 --> 01:08:57,680
I was worried they'd black out and drown.

1464
01:08:57,760 --> 01:08:59,120
Safety team, go!

1465
01:08:59,920 --> 01:09:01,279
Are you stressed?

1466
01:09:01,359 --> 01:09:04,479
A little.
The previous pair set the bar high.

1467
01:09:05,600 --> 01:09:07,200
We'll see how this goes.

1468
01:09:07,279 --> 01:09:09,359
Only four minutes left.

1469
01:09:09,439 --> 01:09:11,000
Do, just relax.

1470
01:09:11,080 --> 01:09:11,920
Take it easy.

1471
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:14,000
I like it. There's real chemistry there.

1472
01:09:14,080 --> 01:09:15,880
They're like a very intense couple.

1473
01:09:15,960 --> 01:09:19,000
- Okay.
- Slowly. Good.

1474
01:09:19,080 --> 01:09:21,640
They're both fighters.
They gave it their all.

1475
01:09:21,720 --> 01:09:24,040
Very good. Slowly now.

1476
01:09:24,120 --> 01:09:26,960
Yeah, take it slow.

1477
01:09:27,040 --> 01:09:31,840
I think they really ran out of air.
That's why they came up.

1478
01:09:31,920 --> 01:09:33,200
I can't do this.

1479
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:35,680
Answer…

1480
01:09:35,760 --> 01:09:37,279
Their dedication is insane.

1481
01:09:37,359 --> 01:09:38,760
That's real spirit.

1482
01:09:38,840 --> 01:09:39,920
Thirty seconds left!

1483
01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:41,040
Can you go again?

1484
01:09:42,800 --> 01:09:45,000
Beautiful.

1485
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:46,279
Okay.

1486
01:09:46,960 --> 01:09:48,399
Their posing looks great.

1487
01:09:48,479 --> 01:09:49,600
They go down together.

1488
01:09:49,680 --> 01:09:52,200
Oh, he's following his partner.

1489
01:09:52,279 --> 01:09:54,000
Beautiful.

1490
01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:56,200
- That's it! Beautiful.
- That gave me chills.

1491
01:09:56,280 --> 01:09:57,360
Relax.

1492
01:09:58,560 --> 01:09:59,520
That's it. Perfect.

1493
01:10:01,480 --> 01:10:03,560
The chemistry is spot-on. They did well.

1494
01:10:03,640 --> 01:10:06,480
You can feel the real connection
between them underwater.

1495
01:10:06,560 --> 01:10:07,600
Time's up!

1496
01:10:07,680 --> 01:10:09,120
Well done.

1497
01:10:09,200 --> 01:10:10,560
Do and Bo.

1498
01:10:10,640 --> 01:10:12,880
- Honestly, Do and Bo might win this.
- Really?

1499
01:10:12,960 --> 01:10:14,560
They're a great team. I love it.

1500
01:10:14,640 --> 01:10:16,720
It was amazing. You should've seen it.

1501
01:10:16,800 --> 01:10:17,840
That was great.

1502
01:10:17,920 --> 01:10:20,120
I honestly thought they wouldn't make it.

1503
01:10:20,200 --> 01:10:21,600
- Incredible.
- So well done.

1504
01:10:21,680 --> 01:10:24,880
They think outside the box.
They'd win hands down for creativity.

1505
01:10:24,960 --> 01:10:26,800
- Taking notes.
- Taking notes.

1506
01:10:27,320 --> 01:10:29,680
- Want to share a breath with me?
- Now?

1507
01:10:29,760 --> 01:10:31,960
I'm already breathless.

1508
01:10:32,040 --> 01:10:33,120
Come closer then.

1509
01:10:35,320 --> 01:10:37,760
Up next are Peem and PP.

1510
01:10:37,840 --> 01:10:39,240
They've got a second chance.

1511
01:10:39,320 --> 01:10:41,520
Peem gets a second chance.

1512
01:10:41,600 --> 01:10:43,600
If everyone's ready, please begin.

1513
01:10:43,680 --> 01:10:47,240
Okay, relax.
Focus on breathing normally first.

1514
01:10:47,320 --> 01:10:49,640
I want them to take it slow
and feel the moment.

1515
01:10:49,720 --> 01:10:51,760
I think their mentor gave them
some guidance.

1516
01:10:51,840 --> 01:10:54,040
But he also let them use their own ideas.

1517
01:10:55,920 --> 01:10:57,040
- Down already?
- Yeah.

1518
01:10:57,760 --> 01:10:59,440
Take it slow.

1519
01:10:59,520 --> 01:11:00,360
Good.

1520
01:11:00,440 --> 01:11:01,760
Nice positioning.

1521
01:11:03,320 --> 01:11:04,480
I'm confused by this.

1522
01:11:04,560 --> 01:11:05,520
It's symbolic.

1523
01:11:05,600 --> 01:11:06,840
Oh, symbolic.

1524
01:11:06,920 --> 01:11:08,920
I don't get why they're doing that.

1525
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:11,640
The judges are confused
about what they're doing too.

1526
01:11:11,720 --> 01:11:13,320
Eight minutes left.

1527
01:11:14,040 --> 01:11:15,080
That's cute.

1528
01:11:15,160 --> 01:11:18,840
PP seems very dedicated to his work.

1529
01:11:18,920 --> 01:11:20,960
But he probably overthinks it.

1530
01:11:22,960 --> 01:11:25,640
Wait, were they just rehearsing
the actions just now?

1531
01:11:26,600 --> 01:11:27,600
Okay, good.

1532
01:11:27,680 --> 01:11:30,440
You can act it out first,
then go in for the kiss.

1533
01:11:30,520 --> 01:11:32,160
Use your body movements.

1534
01:11:32,240 --> 01:11:33,920
Find your killer pose.

1535
01:11:34,000 --> 01:11:38,720
In a challenge like this,
you need a standout moment.

1536
01:11:38,800 --> 01:11:40,160
Take it slow.

1537
01:11:40,880 --> 01:11:43,320
Okay, good. Take it easy.

1538
01:11:43,400 --> 01:11:45,440
Can you keep going while underwater?

1539
01:11:45,520 --> 01:11:46,880
Let's start over.

1540
01:11:46,960 --> 01:11:49,280
Only seven minutes left now.

1541
01:11:49,360 --> 01:11:52,080
Do you need a weight belt?
Are you struggling to sink?

1542
01:11:52,760 --> 01:11:54,960
I think… Do you want a weight belt?

1543
01:11:55,040 --> 01:11:58,880
At first, I thought we'd be fine.
I was worried the belt would show.

1544
01:11:58,960 --> 01:12:01,600
I was worried it would look fake.
So I didn't wear it.

1545
01:12:01,680 --> 01:12:03,840
Take your time, but give me something.

1546
01:12:03,920 --> 01:12:05,960
Pull his head in, like this.

1547
01:12:06,040 --> 01:12:08,440
Right, but let's have you kiss sooner.

1548
01:12:08,520 --> 01:12:11,080
Then go for a second kiss
if you still have enough air.

1549
01:12:11,160 --> 01:12:14,160
It was building up, but it fell short.

1550
01:12:14,240 --> 01:12:16,280
They didn't get enough screen time.

1551
01:12:16,360 --> 01:12:19,360
Let desire guide you,
then drift up and kiss.

1552
01:12:19,440 --> 01:12:21,840
You can pull him down
to keep going underwater.

1553
01:12:21,920 --> 01:12:24,520
Are we still doing the lip touch?

1554
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:25,760
- Yes.
- Okay.

1555
01:12:25,840 --> 01:12:27,640
Let's aim for two good takes.

1556
01:12:27,720 --> 01:12:30,400
During those ten minutes,
we kept adjusting things.

1557
01:12:30,480 --> 01:12:33,280
Mile told us to just kiss to be safe.

1558
01:12:33,360 --> 01:12:36,640
So we went with
what we thought they wanted.

1559
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:38,160
Five minutes left!

1560
01:12:40,800 --> 01:12:42,160
Your thoughts, Mentor Off?

1561
01:12:42,240 --> 01:12:45,640
I'm pretty worried.
We're already halfway through our time.

1562
01:12:45,720 --> 01:12:47,840
No good takes yet. Hoping for the best.

1563
01:12:49,000 --> 01:12:52,400
Take it slow. Good. Great positioning.

1564
01:12:53,000 --> 01:12:54,800
Nice and easy.

1565
01:12:54,880 --> 01:12:56,840
Don't lose eye contact.

1566
01:12:56,920 --> 01:12:58,040
Play around a bit.

1567
01:12:58,120 --> 01:12:59,640
Good. That's cute.

1568
01:13:00,920 --> 01:13:02,800
- Nice.
- Okay.

1569
01:13:02,880 --> 01:13:05,080
That's good. Really good.

1570
01:13:05,160 --> 01:13:06,160
I have chills.

1571
01:13:06,240 --> 01:13:08,840
We didn't do it because
of how we interpreted the brief.

1572
01:13:08,920 --> 01:13:12,160
Sharing a breath
can also be expressed through energy.

1573
01:13:12,240 --> 01:13:14,440
It symbolizes sharing a breath.

1574
01:13:14,520 --> 01:13:16,440
Even without actually kissing.

1575
01:13:16,520 --> 01:13:18,840
It's open to interpretation.

1576
01:13:18,920 --> 01:13:21,520
I don't know if the judges
or mentors will like it.

1577
01:13:21,600 --> 01:13:23,360
Two minutes left!

1578
01:13:23,440 --> 01:13:26,520
Then end with this pose.

1579
01:13:26,600 --> 01:13:27,720
What's wrong?

1580
01:13:27,800 --> 01:13:30,160
- That was great.
- Are you being sincere?

1581
01:13:30,240 --> 01:13:31,400
One hundred percent fake.

1582
01:13:32,160 --> 01:13:33,000
Hundred percent.

1583
01:13:34,840 --> 01:13:37,440
When I'm alone, I can feel it.

1584
01:13:37,520 --> 01:13:40,400
But he steps in as my guiding light.

1585
01:13:40,480 --> 01:13:42,920
Then I swing around.
It'll create a beautiful movement.

1586
01:13:43,000 --> 01:13:44,040
That's what we want.

1587
01:13:44,120 --> 01:13:45,400
Just kiss.

1588
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:47,080
One and a half minutes left!

1589
01:13:47,160 --> 01:13:49,880
Spin slowly. Don't go up yet.

1590
01:13:49,960 --> 01:13:52,640
When working with people,
managing your ego is key.

1591
01:13:52,720 --> 01:13:54,440
At first, I thought

1592
01:13:54,520 --> 01:13:58,280
the pacing was a bit slow,
but it got much better.

1593
01:13:58,360 --> 01:14:02,080
We wanted to pitch an idea
to meet him halfway.

1594
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:04,800
That didn't mean
we wouldn't follow his directions.

1595
01:14:04,880 --> 01:14:06,680
Peem suggested it from the start.

1596
01:14:06,760 --> 01:14:08,600
A beautiful, wide drowning shot.

1597
01:14:08,680 --> 01:14:12,640
But their interaction
wasn't as special as the other pairs'.

1598
01:14:12,720 --> 01:14:15,880
We tried to ease into it
so they wouldn't feel pressured.

1599
01:14:15,960 --> 01:14:17,120
Last minute!

1600
01:14:17,760 --> 01:14:18,920
Take your time.

1601
01:14:19,000 --> 01:14:21,240
Working with Mentor Off
versus Mentor Ananda…

1602
01:14:21,320 --> 01:14:24,640
They're both great.
Mentor Ananda gives you more freedom.

1603
01:14:24,720 --> 01:14:26,800
But Off is clear.
He has a specific vision.

1604
01:14:26,880 --> 01:14:28,160
Mile's vision is clear.

1605
01:14:28,240 --> 01:14:29,480
Tease him.

1606
01:14:29,560 --> 01:14:32,280
Good. Don't go up yet.

1607
01:14:32,360 --> 01:14:33,520
Good.

1608
01:14:34,160 --> 01:14:35,120
Yes, that's better.

1609
01:14:35,200 --> 01:14:36,880
- Better.
- Much better.

1610
01:14:38,400 --> 01:14:39,720
That's good. Very good.

1611
01:14:39,800 --> 01:14:41,960
I'm amazed by the result.

1612
01:14:42,040 --> 01:14:44,600
PP wasn't confident in his swimming.

1613
01:14:44,680 --> 01:14:47,240
But I knew he could do it.
And he pulled it off.

1614
01:14:47,320 --> 01:14:49,200
Their idea was creative,

1615
01:14:49,280 --> 01:14:51,440
but the storytelling did not come through.

1616
01:14:51,520 --> 01:14:53,480
It's a shame. We know they can do better.

1617
01:14:53,560 --> 01:14:54,600
Great job.

1618
01:14:54,680 --> 01:14:56,240
- We got some good takes.
- Which…

1619
01:14:58,680 --> 01:15:01,200
They kept doing the same thing
until time ran out.

1620
01:15:01,280 --> 01:15:04,440
I don't understand it.
What was that supposed to mean?

1621
01:15:04,520 --> 01:15:06,400
Fashion videos need to convey emotion.

1622
01:15:06,920 --> 01:15:09,760
And now, we're down to the final pair
for this campaign.

1623
01:15:09,840 --> 01:15:10,960
Rome and Jacob.

1624
01:15:11,040 --> 01:15:12,080
Watch out.

1625
01:15:12,160 --> 01:15:13,160
- Okay.
- Let's go.

1626
01:15:13,240 --> 01:15:14,440
- When ready.
- Go.

1627
01:15:14,520 --> 01:15:16,400
The dark horses! I forgot.

1628
01:15:17,480 --> 01:15:20,520
Rome and Jacob have great chemistry.
They're very handsome.

1629
01:15:20,600 --> 01:15:22,240
Together, they're a perfect match.

1630
01:15:22,320 --> 01:15:24,120
Just do what we practiced.

1631
01:15:25,240 --> 01:15:26,080
Stay calm.

1632
01:15:26,760 --> 01:15:30,080
I heard Jacob wasn't feeling too well.

1633
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:31,600
Oh, okay.

1634
01:15:33,400 --> 01:15:34,920
That looks so light.

1635
01:15:35,000 --> 01:15:36,880
Hey, hey!

1636
01:15:36,960 --> 01:15:41,960
We briefed them that we wanted a real kiss
based on their underwater positions.

1637
01:15:42,040 --> 01:15:43,360
Wow.

1638
01:15:44,000 --> 01:15:45,560
Beautiful.

1639
01:15:45,640 --> 01:15:48,680
Switch positions a bit. Angle it.

1640
01:15:48,760 --> 01:15:51,240
Toss the buoy. Again. Yes, not bad.

1641
01:15:51,320 --> 01:15:52,720
How many minutes left?

1642
01:15:52,800 --> 01:15:54,640
Right now, six minutes and ten seconds.

1643
01:15:54,720 --> 01:15:56,280
Okay, start when you're ready.

1644
01:15:56,360 --> 01:15:59,800
We know Rome is here to win.

1645
01:15:59,880 --> 01:16:00,920
He's always done well.

1646
01:16:01,000 --> 01:16:03,920
Do you have it?

1647
01:16:04,000 --> 01:16:06,520
- Beautiful. So beautiful.
- Go for it.

1648
01:16:06,600 --> 01:16:08,720
- Looks great.
- Move closer to each other.

1649
01:16:08,800 --> 01:16:09,640
That's good.

1650
01:16:09,720 --> 01:16:10,880
A little more.

1651
01:16:10,960 --> 01:16:12,120
Turn a bit more.

1652
01:16:12,200 --> 01:16:14,920
Go back and kiss. Kiss.

1653
01:16:15,000 --> 01:16:18,320
I hesitated, but Rome just went for it.

1654
01:16:18,400 --> 01:16:22,160
Pull him in for a slow kiss. Go ahead.

1655
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:25,480
I think my slight hesitation
might have driven Rome crazy.

1656
01:16:25,560 --> 01:16:26,960
I don't know if it did.

1657
01:16:27,040 --> 01:16:28,320
Okay.

1658
01:16:28,400 --> 01:16:30,520
Why are they afraid to kiss?

1659
01:16:31,440 --> 01:16:33,560
I think Jacob wanted a magic moment.

1660
01:16:33,640 --> 01:16:36,160
Like when our faces were close.

1661
01:16:36,240 --> 01:16:37,840
It's just a straight guy reaction.

1662
01:16:37,920 --> 01:16:40,240
It's just… ugh.

1663
01:16:40,320 --> 01:16:41,640
They should be outstanding.

1664
01:16:41,720 --> 01:16:43,720
You can't be ordinary.

1665
01:16:43,800 --> 01:16:44,640
Let's see.

1666
01:16:44,720 --> 01:16:46,760
It felt forced
because I've never done this.

1667
01:16:52,080 --> 01:16:53,920
Have them go slowly.

1668
01:16:54,000 --> 01:16:55,280
Three minutes left.

1669
01:16:55,360 --> 01:16:56,680
Okay.

1670
01:16:56,760 --> 01:16:58,440
So beautiful.

1671
01:16:58,520 --> 01:16:59,760
Very beautiful.

1672
01:16:59,840 --> 01:17:02,400
I felt like I wasn't in control of myself.

1673
01:17:02,480 --> 01:17:03,680
Because there was…

1674
01:17:04,720 --> 01:17:06,520
- Slowly.
- A bit more.

1675
01:17:06,600 --> 01:17:08,040
Come up if you can't breathe.

1676
01:17:08,120 --> 01:17:10,480
- It's completely off.
- Give them a chance.

1677
01:17:10,560 --> 01:17:13,280
I think Jacob is still
holding something back.

1678
01:17:13,360 --> 01:17:15,640
He won't fully let go.

1679
01:17:15,720 --> 01:17:19,320
Okay, listen to me this time.
Go down slowly.

1680
01:17:19,400 --> 01:17:21,880
Look at each other and kiss.

1681
01:17:21,960 --> 01:17:24,360
Then pull away slightly.

1682
01:17:24,440 --> 01:17:26,400
Then go in for a deeper kiss.

1683
01:17:26,480 --> 01:17:31,000
Just listen and decide
if Mile would like it or not.

1684
01:17:31,080 --> 01:17:36,200
We might not kiss, but try a new feeling,
a new pose, something like that.

1685
01:17:36,280 --> 01:17:37,480
Forty-five seconds. Go.

1686
01:17:37,560 --> 01:17:39,320
Slowly.

1687
01:17:46,840 --> 01:17:49,760
The voice in my head was saying,
"Right now? Right here?"

1688
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:55,280
Last 30 seconds.

1689
01:17:59,200 --> 01:18:02,440
They're teasing each other.

1690
01:18:02,520 --> 01:18:04,040
Yeah.

1691
01:18:04,120 --> 01:18:07,080
- That's good. I can feel the chemistry.
- Yes, that's better.

1692
01:18:07,160 --> 01:18:08,320
Kiss again. More.

1693
01:18:08,400 --> 01:18:10,280
Mile told us to just kiss.

1694
01:18:10,360 --> 01:18:14,360
I just followed Mile's instructions.
I can do whatever is needed.

1695
01:18:16,160 --> 01:18:18,120
Last 20 seconds.

1696
01:18:21,160 --> 01:18:22,600
They didn't go all the way.

1697
01:18:22,680 --> 01:18:26,600
Whether they kissed or not,
today's case required lips touching.

1698
01:18:26,680 --> 01:18:28,160
To share oxygen.

1699
01:18:28,240 --> 01:18:31,640
That caused a hiccup, which is a shame.

1700
01:18:31,720 --> 01:18:34,920
If they nailed it from the start,
they would have done it faster.

1701
01:18:35,000 --> 01:18:36,160
Time's up!

1702
01:18:36,240 --> 01:18:37,440
Okay.

1703
01:18:37,520 --> 01:18:39,240
- It's okay.
- It's giving me chills.

1704
01:18:39,320 --> 01:18:40,160
It's really good.

1705
01:18:40,240 --> 01:18:41,840
I hope I'll win today.

1706
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:45,720
Our chances of getting a good take
must be higher than the others.

1707
01:18:45,800 --> 01:18:47,440
We have to keep moving forward.

1708
01:18:47,520 --> 01:18:51,120
We can't have limitations
if we want to win.

1709
01:18:52,840 --> 01:18:56,320
Our judges have finished
tallying the scores.

1710
01:18:56,400 --> 01:18:58,440
But before we hear the results,

1711
01:18:58,520 --> 01:19:01,200
let's hear some comments from them.

1712
01:19:01,280 --> 01:19:02,480
The first pair.

1713
01:19:02,560 --> 01:19:04,160
Peem and Mew.

1714
01:19:04,240 --> 01:19:06,360
I think this pair really clicked.

1715
01:19:06,440 --> 01:19:09,200
The message was fully delivered.

1716
01:19:09,280 --> 01:19:11,400
And the chemistry turned out well too.

1717
01:19:11,480 --> 01:19:14,160
They seemed like a great pair.

1718
01:19:14,240 --> 01:19:15,680
Moving on to the second pair.

1719
01:19:15,760 --> 01:19:17,400
Kimhan and Pom.

1720
01:19:17,480 --> 01:19:20,000
This pair had great positional balance.

1721
01:19:20,080 --> 01:19:21,880
Their inner emotions came through.

1722
01:19:21,960 --> 01:19:25,000
They're another pair with great chemistry.

1723
01:19:25,080 --> 01:19:26,320
- Thank you.
- Yes.

1724
01:19:26,400 --> 01:19:29,480
- Good. Kim worked really hard.
- Just like Pom.

1725
01:19:29,560 --> 01:19:32,040
Third pair, Lincoln and Leo.

1726
01:19:32,120 --> 01:19:34,800
Lincoln felt a bit too soft.

1727
01:19:34,880 --> 01:19:38,960
As for Leo, I admire him for doing that
despite his fear of water.

1728
01:19:39,040 --> 01:19:42,360
He fought hard. It was amazing.

1729
01:19:42,440 --> 01:19:45,440
It felt like
he completely overcame his fear.

1730
01:19:45,520 --> 01:19:47,000
This pair really won my heart.

1731
01:19:47,080 --> 01:19:50,840
They took what we gave them
and turned it into a masterpiece.

1732
01:19:50,920 --> 01:19:51,880
I'm happy with it.

1733
01:19:51,960 --> 01:19:54,240
Our fourth pair, Fox and Manyoo.

1734
01:19:54,320 --> 01:19:55,920
Fox seemed a bit confused.

1735
01:19:56,000 --> 01:19:59,240
And it didn't convey the intended message.

1736
01:19:59,320 --> 01:20:03,000
The fourth pair performed the weakest.

1737
01:20:03,080 --> 01:20:05,040
Donut and Bonus.

1738
01:20:05,120 --> 01:20:08,160
I was very surprised by this pair.
I loved them too.

1739
01:20:08,240 --> 01:20:12,560
It was so unexpected.
I can't believe they made it this far.

1740
01:20:12,640 --> 01:20:14,120
Peem and PP.

1741
01:20:14,200 --> 01:20:16,240
There was a lot of hesitation.

1742
01:20:16,320 --> 01:20:17,680
The chemistry wasn't there.

1743
01:20:17,760 --> 01:20:21,440
It's a bit of a shame for Peem
to have two chances in vain.

1744
01:20:21,520 --> 01:20:25,360
I was confused by the hand gestures.
The message didn't come through clearly.

1745
01:20:25,440 --> 01:20:29,720
It made things confusing.
It just felt a bit off.

1746
01:20:29,800 --> 01:20:34,560
The real mistake was holding back.
It's a shame.

1747
01:20:34,640 --> 01:20:37,240
Otherwise, they would've had
much better moments.

1748
01:20:37,320 --> 01:20:39,840
Our final pair, Rome and Jacob.

1749
01:20:39,920 --> 01:20:44,080
Rome and Jacob are another favorite pair.

1750
01:20:44,160 --> 01:20:47,960
They stumbled initially
and took their time.

1751
01:20:48,040 --> 01:20:50,160
But the ending was beautiful.

1752
01:20:50,240 --> 01:20:52,320
The shot where he helped Rome
was stunning.

1753
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:54,040
Chemistry improved towards the end.

1754
01:20:54,120 --> 01:20:58,240
All right, we've heard from our judges.

1755
01:20:58,320 --> 01:21:01,920
It's time to reveal the results.

1756
01:21:02,840 --> 01:21:03,920
- PP.
- Yes.

1757
01:21:04,000 --> 01:21:07,080
Which pair performed the best today?

1758
01:21:07,160 --> 01:21:08,800
Dobo.

1759
01:21:08,880 --> 01:21:10,120
Kimhan and Pom.

1760
01:21:10,800 --> 01:21:12,640
Kimhan, Pom.

1761
01:21:14,760 --> 01:21:16,080
Kimhan and Pom.

1762
01:21:16,160 --> 01:21:17,680
Wow.

1763
01:21:17,760 --> 01:21:19,240
- Okay.
- Okay.

1764
01:21:19,320 --> 01:21:20,640
We met halfway.

1765
01:21:20,720 --> 01:21:23,480
Both of them sparked that chemistry.

1766
01:21:23,560 --> 01:21:26,800
Honestly, either of them deserves it now.

1767
01:21:26,880 --> 01:21:29,400
Oh no, don't lose to them again.

1768
01:21:29,480 --> 01:21:32,000
I just can't stand looking at them.

1769
01:21:32,680 --> 01:21:36,400
I did the best I could. I just kept quiet.
Many had things to deal with.

1770
01:21:36,480 --> 01:21:39,040
Otherwise, I couldn't move forward.

1771
01:21:39,120 --> 01:21:43,360
All right, let's hear
some comments from the judges.

1772
01:21:43,440 --> 01:21:45,080
Starting with PP.

1773
01:21:45,160 --> 01:21:48,160
The very first take was my favorite.

1774
01:21:48,240 --> 01:21:50,360
It conveyed everything perfectly.

1775
01:21:50,440 --> 01:21:52,680
This pair delivered the most.

1776
01:21:52,760 --> 01:21:54,320
I couldn't pick between them.

1777
01:21:54,400 --> 01:21:56,840
Because if they hadn't
supported each other,

1778
01:21:56,920 --> 01:21:58,680
they wouldn't have come this far.

1779
01:21:58,760 --> 01:22:01,680
Kimhan projected well,
which allowed Pom to give his all.

1780
01:22:01,760 --> 01:22:05,360
If it weren't these two acting together,
the work might not be this good.

1781
01:22:05,440 --> 01:22:07,800
They clearly brought out
the best in each other.

1782
01:22:07,880 --> 01:22:10,720
I didn't want the judges
to have to choose.

1783
01:22:10,800 --> 01:22:12,000
It was a pure 50-50 split.

1784
01:22:12,080 --> 01:22:13,720
And what about Pom?

1785
01:22:13,800 --> 01:22:15,360
Personally or professionally?

1786
01:22:15,440 --> 01:22:17,600
- What?
- Hey, calm down.

1787
01:22:17,680 --> 01:22:18,880
Go ahead, PP.

1788
01:22:18,960 --> 01:22:20,160
Absolutely loved it.

1789
01:22:20,240 --> 01:22:21,880
- The performance?
- Right.

1790
01:22:21,960 --> 01:22:23,600
Let's stick to the performance.

1791
01:22:23,680 --> 01:22:25,280
The performance.

1792
01:22:25,360 --> 01:22:27,240
He seemed very dedicated.

1793
01:22:27,320 --> 01:22:32,080
They really fed off each other's energy.
The reaction was right.

1794
01:22:32,160 --> 01:22:35,280
When they act together,
their paces aligned.

1795
01:22:35,360 --> 01:22:38,120
They have great chemistry.

1796
01:22:38,200 --> 01:22:39,440
I loved it.

1797
01:22:39,520 --> 01:22:42,720
Today, there will be only one winner.

1798
01:22:42,800 --> 01:22:45,240
- Just one.
- Only one team can win.

1799
01:22:45,320 --> 01:22:47,920
It feels like waiting for a pageant crown.

1800
01:22:48,000 --> 01:22:49,280
- Yeah.
- Okay.

1801
01:22:49,360 --> 01:22:54,200
PP, the winner of
"The Spirit of Unity" campaign is…

1802
01:22:57,360 --> 01:22:58,280
Kimhan.

1803
01:22:58,360 --> 01:23:00,200
Woo!

1804
01:23:00,760 --> 01:23:02,240
Winning makes it all worth it.

1805
01:23:02,320 --> 01:23:05,400
I'm so proud of him,
and it reflects on me too.

1806
01:23:05,480 --> 01:23:08,320
I'm surprised by how proud I feel.

1807
01:23:08,400 --> 01:23:10,320
Today is truly my day.

1808
01:23:11,680 --> 01:23:13,120
I agree. I accept the result.

1809
01:23:13,200 --> 01:23:16,120
But Pom was an amazing runner-up.

1810
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:19,720
Honestly, this is the hardest campaign
since I joined <i>The Face</i>.

1811
01:23:20,520 --> 01:23:22,640
They are great,
and I respect their spirit.

1812
01:23:22,720 --> 01:23:24,680
I didn't expect them to be this bold.

1813
01:23:24,760 --> 01:23:27,240
He fought hard and went all out.

1814
01:23:27,320 --> 01:23:30,040
Like Leo, he surpassed all boundaries.

1815
01:23:30,120 --> 01:23:33,400
I was amazed by how fiercely they fought.

1816
01:23:33,480 --> 01:23:35,800
It wasn't just about earning the skills.

1817
01:23:35,880 --> 01:23:40,800
They had to battle each other too,
which makes me even prouder.

1818
01:23:40,880 --> 01:23:44,520
And of course, today,
we must thank our judges

1819
01:23:44,600 --> 01:23:45,920
- for joining us.
- Thank you.

1820
01:23:46,000 --> 01:23:48,280
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

1821
01:23:48,360 --> 01:23:53,160
Also, a big thank you to Joong today.

1822
01:23:53,240 --> 01:23:55,240
Thank you to our three mentors.

1823
01:23:55,320 --> 01:23:57,600
Mentor Off, Mentor Ananda,
and Mentor Mile.

1824
01:23:57,680 --> 01:23:59,360
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

1825
01:23:59,440 --> 01:24:01,120
I have to hand it to Kim.

1826
01:24:01,200 --> 01:24:02,840
He deserves a round of applause.

1827
01:24:02,920 --> 01:24:06,240
But we didn't lose.
As I said, we just didn't win.

1828
01:24:06,320 --> 01:24:08,720
I guess I'll just play the nosy neighbor.

1829
01:25:00,480 --> 01:25:03,000
- Yeah.
- Hello. Good to see you.

1830
01:25:03,080 --> 01:25:04,760
- Hello.
- Hello.

1831
01:25:04,840 --> 01:25:07,800
When Mile walked in,
I knew there'd be trouble.

1832
01:25:07,880 --> 01:25:11,760
I could tell from his eyes
that he was mad.

1833
01:25:11,840 --> 01:25:15,040
Oh, there were many things.
Let's just put it this way.

1834
01:25:15,120 --> 01:25:18,000
Our team didn't win. Okay.

1835
01:25:18,080 --> 01:25:21,920
- You probably knew that already.
- It was so scary and tense.

1836
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:24,520
I wasn't furious. Was I displeased? Yes.

1837
01:25:24,600 --> 01:25:27,000
Let's clear the air individually
on any issues.

1838
01:25:27,080 --> 01:25:30,320
Yesterday's performance
didn't reflect well enough.

1839
01:25:30,400 --> 01:25:31,960
It didn't reflect the potential

1840
01:25:32,040 --> 01:25:34,960
I see in each of you, you know?

1841
01:25:35,040 --> 01:25:36,720
Why couldn't you kiss? I'm curious.

1842
01:25:36,800 --> 01:25:38,560
I've never done it before.

1843
01:25:38,640 --> 01:25:43,040
I think if I had more experience,
I might do better.

1844
01:25:43,120 --> 01:25:47,400
It wasn't a deep French kiss
or anything crazy like that, you know?

1845
01:25:47,480 --> 01:25:51,320
I'm disappointed in myself
because if I had put in more effort,

1846
01:25:51,400 --> 01:25:53,960
I could've created that special moment.

1847
01:25:54,040 --> 01:25:56,640
That's irrelevant for an actor. Otherwise…

1848
01:25:56,720 --> 01:25:59,680
if you play a murderer,
do you have to actually murder someone?

1849
01:25:59,760 --> 01:26:02,240
You too, Manyoo. What happened yesterday?

1850
01:26:02,320 --> 01:26:06,680
I completely blanked on everything
I prepared yesterday.

1851
01:26:06,760 --> 01:26:08,400
Why did you blank?

1852
01:26:08,480 --> 01:26:15,000
Fox came up so fast,
and I went down and rushed everything.

1853
01:26:15,080 --> 01:26:16,760
Opportunities like this are rare.

1854
01:26:16,840 --> 01:26:21,800
I chose all of you
because I thought you'd fight for it.

1855
01:26:22,880 --> 01:26:25,400
He seemed really impatient.

1856
01:26:25,480 --> 01:26:27,840
If he's still correcting us,

1857
01:26:27,920 --> 01:26:30,920
it means he still wants us on his team.

1858
01:26:51,960 --> 01:26:53,960
Your turn. How was yesterday?

1859
01:26:54,640 --> 01:26:56,720
I did my best.

1860
01:26:56,800 --> 01:26:59,200
I took care of both of my partners.

1861
01:26:59,280 --> 01:27:02,480
But it turned out
I was just supporting them

1862
01:27:02,560 --> 01:27:04,200
instead of shining myself.

1863
01:27:04,280 --> 01:27:06,560
I know you want to win, Peem.

1864
01:27:06,640 --> 01:27:08,920
But if you can't manage your expectations,

1865
01:27:09,000 --> 01:27:11,640
it's going to destroy you.

1866
01:27:11,720 --> 01:27:13,680
- You know that, right?
- Yes.

1867
01:27:13,760 --> 01:27:16,160
We should be the team that others fear.

1868
01:27:16,240 --> 01:27:18,480
Not the team that disappoints the mentor.

1869
01:27:18,560 --> 01:27:22,720
So who do you think is going
to the Black Room today?

1870
01:27:22,800 --> 01:27:25,040
Let me choose for you, okay?

1871
01:27:26,080 --> 01:27:27,880
Everyone else made very few mistakes.

1872
01:27:27,960 --> 01:27:31,400
But I made the most mistakes in the team.

1873
01:27:31,480 --> 01:27:33,560
I hate seeing him disappointed.

1874
01:27:33,640 --> 01:27:37,880
But I get it.
He had high expectations for us.

1875
01:27:38,680 --> 01:27:43,240
Mile must have his reasons
for picking someone for the Black Room.

1876
01:27:43,320 --> 01:27:45,480
I don't want anyone from my team to go.

1877
01:27:51,240 --> 01:27:52,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

1878
01:27:53,000 --> 01:27:55,200
- Why so happy today?
- Just feeling bright.

1879
01:27:55,280 --> 01:27:56,760
Off is acting weird.

1880
01:27:56,840 --> 01:28:00,080
He came in a great mood today.
It shocked everyone.

1881
01:28:00,160 --> 01:28:02,760
I instantly knew it was a bad sign.

1882
01:28:02,840 --> 01:28:05,640
I really want to discuss how you all did.

1883
01:28:05,720 --> 01:28:07,320
Let's start with Mew.

1884
01:28:07,400 --> 01:28:09,600
Ten minutes, seven takes.

1885
01:28:09,680 --> 01:28:11,560
I never thought you'd fight this hard.

1886
01:28:11,640 --> 01:28:15,200
But the downside is
you were still rushing it.

1887
01:28:15,280 --> 01:28:16,760
Fix that, and it'll be perfect.

1888
01:28:16,840 --> 01:28:21,120
Bonus, your poses were arguably the best.

1889
01:28:21,200 --> 01:28:22,040
But…

1890
01:28:23,640 --> 01:28:25,560
what I didn't like is that
it was too fast.

1891
01:28:25,640 --> 01:28:28,640
I was so stressed at the time.
I didn't really listen to anyone.

1892
01:28:28,720 --> 01:28:31,600
I was just focused on
whether I'd end up in the Black Room.

1893
01:28:31,680 --> 01:28:34,080
Next, Rome. You were great.

1894
01:28:34,160 --> 01:28:38,560
Your partner might not
have been very professional.

1895
01:28:38,640 --> 01:28:42,120
That's fine. You did your best.
It's out of your hands now.

1896
01:28:42,200 --> 01:28:44,720
Fox and Manyoo
also seemed very determined.

1897
01:28:44,800 --> 01:28:47,000
You guys looked like you tried your best.

1898
01:28:47,080 --> 01:28:49,000
I just felt that

1899
01:28:49,080 --> 01:28:51,880
the moments during rehearsal
compared to the actual shoot…

1900
01:28:51,960 --> 01:28:54,000
It felt really uncomfortable on set.

1901
01:28:54,080 --> 01:28:56,680
- Were you panicking underwater?
- A little.

1902
01:28:56,760 --> 01:28:59,160
- Wait, didn't you plan it out?
- Yeah, we did.

1903
01:28:59,240 --> 01:29:03,200
But things happened so fast
that we couldn't keep up.

1904
01:29:03,280 --> 01:29:06,160
But the final result is fine.
It's actually quite good.

1905
01:29:06,240 --> 01:29:10,440
Next. You already know
you did well, right?

1906
01:29:10,520 --> 01:29:14,360
I know, but I still feel
a bit disappointed in myself.

1907
01:29:14,440 --> 01:29:18,280
Looking back,
I could've done so much better.

1908
01:29:18,360 --> 01:29:21,480
From what I saw, it was already great.

1909
01:29:21,560 --> 01:29:24,800
I honestly have nothing to criticize.

1910
01:29:24,880 --> 01:29:29,360
And the winning fashion video
belongs to Pom.

1911
01:29:30,520 --> 01:29:31,560
Me?

1912
01:29:32,520 --> 01:29:35,720
But the actual winner is Kimhan.

1913
01:29:35,800 --> 01:29:39,520
I'm happy, but the catch is
I didn't actually win.

1914
01:29:39,600 --> 01:29:41,960
I'm part of the winning pair,
not first place.

1915
01:29:42,040 --> 01:29:45,000
Channel that frustration, Pom. Keep it.

1916
01:29:45,080 --> 01:29:47,320
You'll have plenty more opportunities.

1917
01:29:51,920 --> 01:29:53,400
How's everyone doing?

1918
01:29:53,480 --> 01:29:56,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

1919
01:29:56,360 --> 01:29:58,760
He came in looking so stern. I thought,

1920
01:29:58,840 --> 01:30:01,280
"Is today not going to be our day again?"

1921
01:30:01,360 --> 01:30:03,320
We have some time to talk. Let's start.

1922
01:30:03,400 --> 01:30:05,120
PP, you first.

1923
01:30:05,200 --> 01:30:07,320
I wasn't used to it at first

1924
01:30:07,400 --> 01:30:09,720
since neither of us practiced
in the water.

1925
01:30:09,800 --> 01:30:12,680
But once we put on goggles and went under,
it got a lot better.

1926
01:30:13,400 --> 01:30:16,120
As for you, PP, I'd suggest

1927
01:30:16,800 --> 01:30:20,880
that you should add
a bit more acting into it.

1928
01:30:20,960 --> 01:30:23,160
What do you think, Do? How was it?

1929
01:30:23,240 --> 01:30:26,840
I think the poses underwater
went exactly as I had envisioned.

1930
01:30:26,920 --> 01:30:28,720
The effort is good,

1931
01:30:28,800 --> 01:30:32,280
but we have to be careful
it doesn't turn into stress.

1932
01:30:32,360 --> 01:30:34,440
For me, it looked a bit too tense.

1933
01:30:34,520 --> 01:30:36,360
Kim, tell me, how was it?

1934
01:30:36,440 --> 01:30:39,440
At first, Pom and I
planned it out quite well.

1935
01:30:39,520 --> 01:30:41,800
We had a lot of ideas.

1936
01:30:41,880 --> 01:30:43,680
Overall, I think it was okay.

1937
01:30:43,760 --> 01:30:46,000
Between you and Pom,
who do you think did better?

1938
01:30:46,080 --> 01:30:47,360
I think I did.

1939
01:30:47,440 --> 01:30:50,360
I have to admit, you did a great job.

1940
01:30:50,440 --> 01:30:54,520
But to be completely honest,
Pom also did very well.

1941
01:30:54,600 --> 01:30:56,560
- Everybody praised Pom as well.
- Right.

1942
01:30:56,640 --> 01:30:59,200
It made me stressed.
I can't afford to lose anymore.

1943
01:30:59,280 --> 01:31:01,080
I absolutely can't lose. I have to win.

1944
01:31:01,160 --> 01:31:04,920
Lincoln, tell me. How did it go?

1945
01:31:05,000 --> 01:31:06,760
It was pretty challenging yesterday.

1946
01:31:06,840 --> 01:31:11,120
Because before the set,
Leo said I would be underwater

1947
01:31:11,200 --> 01:31:14,040
for no more than five to six seconds.

1948
01:31:14,120 --> 01:31:16,560
It made me a little stressed.

1949
01:31:16,640 --> 01:31:19,800
Okay, congratulations, everyone.
You all did well.

1950
01:31:19,880 --> 01:31:22,080
I have to apologize to you guys.

1951
01:31:23,120 --> 01:31:25,120
That all four of you…

1952
01:31:29,840 --> 01:31:31,520
will have to…

1953
01:31:32,240 --> 01:31:35,360
keep putting up with me
because we fucking won!

1954
01:31:39,560 --> 01:31:41,520
Come here. Congratulations!

1955
01:31:43,880 --> 01:31:45,760
I'm totally energized right now.

1956
01:31:45,840 --> 01:31:46,920
Yes!

1957
01:31:47,520 --> 01:31:49,520
I was actually about to cry.

1958
01:31:49,600 --> 01:31:52,520
Tears of joy. But seeing someone cry more,
not sure what to do.

1959
01:31:52,600 --> 01:31:55,880
Donut completely stole my thunder!
I was the winner!

1960
01:31:55,960 --> 01:31:58,120
You wouldn't even let me have my moment.

1961
01:31:59,840 --> 01:32:03,440
I've actually already decided
who's going to the Black Room.

1962
01:32:03,520 --> 01:32:06,720
One person from our team
is definitely at risk of going home.

1963
01:32:06,800 --> 01:32:10,800
Out of all the videos that made it
to the final four,

1964
01:32:10,880 --> 01:32:12,280
they were all our guys.

1965
01:32:12,360 --> 01:32:14,720
So, for the ones
who didn't make the top four,

1966
01:32:14,800 --> 01:32:18,160
I consider that
you just didn't try hard enough.

1967
01:32:18,240 --> 01:32:20,560
If your name isn't here,
you should know why.

1968
01:32:20,640 --> 01:32:22,080
Okay, Pom made it.

1969
01:32:22,160 --> 01:32:23,200
Mew made it.

1970
01:32:24,160 --> 01:32:25,360
Bo made it.

1971
01:32:25,440 --> 01:32:26,360
Rome made it.

1972
01:32:26,440 --> 01:32:30,000
But Fox, you have to admit that
you're just not as good as the others.

1973
01:32:30,080 --> 01:32:33,560
I don't want to send you to your death.
I want you to put up a fight.

1974
01:32:33,640 --> 01:32:35,560
- Come here, Fox.
- You got this.

1975
01:32:35,640 --> 01:32:37,200
Come on, Fox. Come back to us.

1976
01:32:37,280 --> 01:32:38,840
- Right.
- You can make it, Fox.

1977
01:32:38,920 --> 01:32:40,920
- One, two, three!
- Team Off!

1978
01:32:41,520 --> 01:32:44,520
It's up to him now
to show how much he wants this.

1979
01:32:44,600 --> 01:32:47,680
If Fox comes back,
I'll be waiting with open arms.

1980
01:32:48,480 --> 01:32:50,800
Ready to give him a big hug.

1981
01:32:50,880 --> 01:32:53,480
Honestly, I was disappointed
in all of you yesterday.

1982
01:32:53,560 --> 01:32:59,360
But I still want you all to get
as much airtime on the show as possible.

1983
01:32:59,440 --> 01:33:03,440
Team Off will probably send Fox.

1984
01:33:03,520 --> 01:33:06,600
You were underwater with Fox yesterday.
How was it?

1985
01:33:06,680 --> 01:33:09,320
Do you think you can beat him
if I send you?

1986
01:33:09,400 --> 01:33:12,480
There's nothing left to do
but prove myself.

1987
01:33:12,560 --> 01:33:14,400
But I'm sending you in today.

1988
01:33:14,480 --> 01:33:17,560
If he sends Fox, you guys were
paired up yesterday anyway.

1989
01:33:18,080 --> 01:33:19,560
He probably won't eliminate you.

1990
01:33:19,640 --> 01:33:23,080
I was the hope of the team
for this campaign, but I fell short.

1991
01:33:23,160 --> 01:33:25,920
And because of that,
Manyoo is being sent in.

1992
01:33:26,000 --> 01:33:28,000
I don't want anyone to go home.

1993
01:33:28,080 --> 01:33:30,520
Show me I didn't make a mistake.

1994
01:33:31,120 --> 01:33:32,800
That's all. Off you go.

1995
01:33:32,880 --> 01:33:34,280
- See you, Mile.
- Yeah.

1996
01:33:34,880 --> 01:33:36,560
I don't want Manyoo gone.

1997
01:33:36,640 --> 01:33:38,960
I just want him to be stronger.

1998
01:33:39,040 --> 01:33:40,680
He keeps saying he did his best.

1999
01:33:40,760 --> 01:33:43,960
But if his best only gets him this far,

2000
01:33:44,040 --> 01:33:45,880
how is he going to grow?

2001
01:34:10,400 --> 01:34:11,600
Hello.

2002
01:34:13,040 --> 01:34:14,720
Hello.

2003
01:34:17,000 --> 01:34:18,200
You have anything to say?

2004
01:34:18,280 --> 01:34:22,480
I'd like to ask for a chance
to redeem myself, Ananda.

2005
01:34:22,560 --> 01:34:26,360
I want you to know that
in every previous round,

2006
01:34:26,440 --> 01:34:30,000
since the first day I walked in here,
I've always done my best.

2007
01:34:31,320 --> 01:34:34,560
I don't want excuses.
I want to know what happened.

2008
01:34:34,640 --> 01:34:36,360
You're here because of yesterday.

2009
01:34:36,440 --> 01:34:38,920
Because it wasn't you
who messed up the previous week.

2010
01:34:39,000 --> 01:34:42,120
- Right?
- No, it was Gluf the week before.

2011
01:34:42,200 --> 01:34:43,920
Well, is that fair then?

2012
01:34:44,000 --> 01:34:46,800
I honestly don't think it's fair.

2013
01:34:46,880 --> 01:34:49,920
Since you didn't even take the test,
you automatically failed.

2014
01:34:50,440 --> 01:34:52,760
- Let's get back to the two of you.
- Yes, sir.

2015
01:34:52,840 --> 01:34:53,880
Explain yesterday.

2016
01:34:53,960 --> 01:34:56,600
I also think we should have done better.

2017
01:34:56,680 --> 01:35:01,120
No, I'm asking what you think
everyone else saw.

2018
01:35:01,200 --> 01:35:05,200
I don't think they saw
what we were trying to portray.

2019
01:35:05,280 --> 01:35:07,360
You're not answering me. Let me tell you.

2020
01:35:07,440 --> 01:35:10,280
- I saw two people sinking.
- Yes.

2021
01:35:10,360 --> 01:35:13,720
While nibbling at each other like fish.

2022
01:35:13,800 --> 01:35:16,960
It didn't even look like a kiss to me.

2023
01:35:17,040 --> 01:35:20,720
I feel like at that moment,
we should've communicated more.

2024
01:35:20,800 --> 01:35:23,640
Like, "What should we do differently
on the next dive?"

2025
01:35:23,720 --> 01:35:26,320
I understand that.
You're talking about intentions again.

2026
01:35:26,400 --> 01:35:28,600
I just want to know
if you can analyze yourself.

2027
01:35:28,680 --> 01:35:33,320
Because self-analysis is a part of
self-improvement. Do you understand?

2028
01:35:33,400 --> 01:35:37,960
If you can't analyze yourself,
you won't see how others perceive you.

2029
01:35:38,040 --> 01:35:42,720
I had very little underwater experience,
and I was panicking.

2030
01:35:42,800 --> 01:35:46,840
I tried my absolute best.
I did everything I could, and…

2031
01:35:46,920 --> 01:35:50,720
No, but honestly, the result looked
exactly the same almost every time.

2032
01:35:50,800 --> 01:35:52,760
I asked you
a very simple question earlier.

2033
01:35:52,840 --> 01:35:55,080
I feel like
this might be your main problem.

2034
01:35:55,160 --> 01:35:56,480
All right, Fox.

2035
01:35:56,560 --> 01:35:58,920
I've made mistakes in the past.

2036
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:01,280
But every mistake makes me better.

2037
01:36:01,360 --> 01:36:02,720
You can improve?

2038
01:36:02,800 --> 01:36:04,760
I can definitely do better.

2039
01:36:04,840 --> 01:36:09,040
It's like talking to a wall.
You sound like you're reading a script.

2040
01:36:09,120 --> 01:36:11,440
Where's your fighting spirit?

2041
01:36:11,520 --> 01:36:14,840
If that's all you have to say, fine.
It's my job to eliminate someone.

2042
01:36:14,920 --> 01:36:17,720
I need you to dig a little deeper. Try it.

2043
01:36:17,800 --> 01:36:20,440
Honestly, is that my job?
You're not even on my team.

2044
01:36:20,520 --> 01:36:22,680
I'm still wondering
why I'm even helping you.

2045
01:36:22,760 --> 01:36:25,160
All right, I'll give you one more chance.

2046
01:36:25,240 --> 01:36:27,720
Why should you stay on <i>The Face</i>?

2047
01:36:27,800 --> 01:36:29,760
I've been trying hard my whole life.

2048
01:36:29,840 --> 01:36:31,600
I'm an athlete.

2049
01:36:31,680 --> 01:36:34,600
I've already proven once
that I could be the national champion.

2050
01:36:34,680 --> 01:36:37,440
I believe I can improve
even more if I stay.

2051
01:36:37,520 --> 01:36:39,600
But everyone here is trying hard, right?

2052
01:36:39,680 --> 01:36:41,080
- I feel like--
- Right now…

2053
01:36:41,160 --> 01:36:43,280
Can you give me a better reason?

2054
01:36:43,360 --> 01:36:46,600
- Or do you just want to quit?
- No, I don't want to leave.

2055
01:36:46,680 --> 01:36:47,800
I want to stay.

2056
01:36:47,880 --> 01:36:49,480
Should I eliminate both of you?

2057
01:36:49,560 --> 01:36:52,320
What do you gain from being here?

2058
01:36:52,400 --> 01:36:55,200
- A lot. Experience.
- Like what?

2059
01:36:55,280 --> 01:36:57,680
Modeling experience. Everything, really.

2060
01:36:57,760 --> 01:36:59,560
Do you really see its value, Fox?

2061
01:36:59,640 --> 01:37:00,560
I really do.

2062
01:37:00,640 --> 01:37:04,560
After this show,
listening to critiques about my flaws…

2063
01:37:04,640 --> 01:37:07,320
and applying what I learn here
to the real world

2064
01:37:07,400 --> 01:37:08,800
will definitely take me far.

2065
01:37:08,880 --> 01:37:12,760
Because I want to be
an actor in the industry.

2066
01:37:12,840 --> 01:37:14,400
I want to gain experience here.

2067
01:37:14,480 --> 01:37:17,280
Show me this energy next time.
Don't just save it for me.

2068
01:37:17,360 --> 01:37:19,480
You need to maintain this energy.

2069
01:37:19,560 --> 01:37:20,680
And you?

2070
01:37:20,760 --> 01:37:24,880
I've been giving it my all
since I joined <i>The Face</i>.

2071
01:37:24,960 --> 01:37:26,840
I want to keep improving.

2072
01:37:26,920 --> 01:37:30,440
I listen to everyone and ask
how I can get better.

2073
01:37:30,520 --> 01:37:34,200
Hold on. You said you gave it your all,
yet here you are.

2074
01:37:34,280 --> 01:37:36,880
At least I know I tried my best.

2075
01:37:36,960 --> 01:37:39,680
And there's always room to grow.

2076
01:37:39,760 --> 01:37:41,400
You believe that you can do better.

2077
01:37:41,480 --> 01:37:42,320
Yes.

2078
01:37:46,560 --> 01:37:48,560
I'll say it again.

2079
01:37:49,560 --> 01:37:53,040
When you walked in,
you had absolutely zero energy.

2080
01:37:53,120 --> 01:37:56,160
Just go home if that's your vibe.

2081
01:37:56,240 --> 01:37:57,720
It's a waste of everyone's time.

2082
01:37:57,800 --> 01:37:59,840
A waste of the mentors' time.

2083
01:38:02,760 --> 01:38:05,120
I'm sorry, Fox.

2084
01:38:05,880 --> 01:38:07,720
You are not The Face.

2085
01:38:07,800 --> 01:38:09,200
Thank you.

2086
01:38:11,200 --> 01:38:15,280
But at least you finally
showed me something just now.

2087
01:38:15,360 --> 01:38:16,200
Yes.

2088
01:38:22,120 --> 01:38:24,960
I'm sad, but I have no regrets.

2089
01:38:25,040 --> 01:38:28,800
I'll work on my flaws.
I want to thank Mentor Off.

2090
01:38:28,880 --> 01:38:32,280
Thank you for the great opportunity
and experience.

2091
01:38:32,360 --> 01:38:36,960
I'll be rooting for Mentor Off
to reach the Final Walk and…

2092
01:38:37,040 --> 01:38:38,800
take home the win.

2093
01:38:42,440 --> 01:38:44,160
Wait, did he eliminate both?

2094
01:38:44,240 --> 01:38:46,200
- What?
- Congratulations on your win.

2095
01:38:46,280 --> 01:38:49,800
- Nothing's happened yet.
- Nothing, I'm just applauding you.

2096
01:38:49,880 --> 01:38:53,360
Congratulations on your win today.

2097
01:38:53,440 --> 01:38:56,600
Hello. Why is it so tense in here?

2098
01:38:56,680 --> 01:38:58,440
You're the only one who's tense.

2099
01:38:58,520 --> 01:39:01,000
- No tension here at all.
- No tension here.

2100
01:39:01,080 --> 01:39:03,360
- <i>Someone's very excited, Ananda.</i>
- Oh, hello.

2101
01:39:03,440 --> 01:39:06,160
- <i>It's Mentor Off.</i>
- Oh, yes. That's me.

2102
01:39:06,240 --> 01:39:07,480
That's me.

2103
01:39:07,560 --> 01:39:10,680
Why is Mentor Pancake on a video call?
I'm confused.

2104
01:39:11,240 --> 01:39:14,520
Hold on. I'm a bit surprised.
Why wasn't it Gluf?

2105
01:39:14,600 --> 01:39:15,600
I don't get it.

2106
01:39:15,680 --> 01:39:17,680
I thought Gluf was going in, not Manyoo.

2107
01:39:17,760 --> 01:39:21,680
Looking at yesterday's performance,
I felt Manyoo…

2108
01:39:21,760 --> 01:39:26,120
couldn't let go of the fear
an actor shouldn't have.

2109
01:39:26,200 --> 01:39:27,560
I wanted him to prove himself.

2110
01:39:27,640 --> 01:39:29,040
I didn't want Manyoo to leave.

2111
01:39:29,120 --> 01:39:31,080
But I wanted him to get stronger.

2112
01:39:31,160 --> 01:39:33,760
- What a surprise.
- It's like skipping an exam.

2113
01:39:33,840 --> 01:39:35,960
If you don't show up, you get a zero.

2114
01:39:36,040 --> 01:39:38,360
Just let him talk.
I don't need to say anything.

2115
01:39:38,440 --> 01:39:41,720
<i>We shouldn't really have to talk much</i>
<i>since you already sent him.</i>

2116
01:39:41,800 --> 01:39:44,080
<i>It means</i>
<i>you were ready to lose him, right?</i>

2117
01:39:44,160 --> 01:39:46,400
I wasn't ready to lose anyone.

2118
01:39:46,480 --> 01:39:48,240
<i>But you did lose.</i>

2119
01:39:48,320 --> 01:39:50,520
Right, I lost to you.

2120
01:39:50,600 --> 01:39:52,280
But your victory today…

2121
01:39:52,360 --> 01:39:54,920
wouldn't have been possible
without Pom's assistance.

2122
01:39:55,000 --> 01:39:58,200
Understand that the best runner-up
is still just the runner-up.

2123
01:39:58,280 --> 01:39:59,320
Okay, understood.

2124
01:39:59,400 --> 01:40:01,640
In the end, he let Kimhan win.

2125
01:40:01,720 --> 01:40:04,200
- Okay.
- Hey, really, thank you, Pom.

2126
01:40:04,280 --> 01:40:05,280
I agree.

2127
01:40:05,360 --> 01:40:06,640
We won this together.

2128
01:40:06,720 --> 01:40:09,840
Because Kimhan's partner was Pom.

2129
01:40:09,920 --> 01:40:14,280
They matched
each other's energy perfectly.

2130
01:40:14,360 --> 01:40:17,640
He helped me, but didn't I help him too?

2131
01:40:17,720 --> 01:40:20,160
- Come here. Let me smell the winner.
- Go ahead, smell.

2132
01:40:20,240 --> 01:40:21,600
Okay.

2133
01:40:22,840 --> 01:40:24,440
Does victory smell sweet?

2134
01:40:24,520 --> 01:40:26,240
Get used to it.

2135
01:40:26,320 --> 01:40:28,280
He's here to show off his win.

2136
01:40:28,360 --> 01:40:31,000
It's your day. I'll give you two.
Yesterday and today.

2137
01:40:31,080 --> 01:40:34,240
Hope it happens again
so I can smell your armpits.

2138
01:40:34,320 --> 01:40:37,720
<i>Have you chosen someone, Ananda?</i>
<i>I'm dying to know.</i>

2139
01:40:37,800 --> 01:40:40,000
<i>Go all out, Daddy. Go for it.</i>

2140
01:40:40,080 --> 01:40:41,560
Don't make that face, Pan.

2141
01:40:43,600 --> 01:40:48,640
At the time, I was very confident
that Manyoo would make a comeback.

2142
01:40:54,640 --> 01:40:55,800
Thank you.

2143
01:40:55,880 --> 01:40:59,400
Congratulations to Mile for talking
his way out of the Black Room twice.

2144
01:40:59,480 --> 01:41:01,960
I'm sad. I'm sad that…

2145
01:41:02,040 --> 01:41:04,680
we lost a teammate.

2146
01:41:04,760 --> 01:41:07,080
Gosh, I feel so bad for Fox.

2147
01:41:07,160 --> 01:41:09,880
I really pity Off's team.

2148
01:41:09,960 --> 01:41:11,880
Can I get a tissue? I'm going to cry.

2149
01:41:11,960 --> 01:41:13,160
I'm still sad right now.

2150
01:41:13,240 --> 01:41:15,640
But soon, that sadness will turn into

2151
01:41:15,720 --> 01:41:17,840
vengeance, and I'll get even.

2152
01:41:17,920 --> 01:41:20,320
By saving them, you still have five left.

2153
01:41:20,400 --> 01:41:24,400
It'll be even harder.
Keep fighting, Mile! Keep fighting.

2154
01:41:24,480 --> 01:41:26,080
I want my boys to improve too.

2155
01:41:26,160 --> 01:41:29,200
They got saved twice.
His boys might be all talk.

2156
01:41:29,280 --> 01:41:31,000
But lacking in actual skills.

2157
01:41:31,080 --> 01:41:35,360
<i>Tell Mentor Mile to fight harder.</i>
<i>It'll make the competition more fun.</i>

2158
01:41:35,440 --> 01:41:39,800
Sure. If you count the boys
and mentors, we're even.

2159
01:41:39,880 --> 01:41:44,600
You have two mentors, I have five kids.
Do the math, it's exactly the same.

2160
01:41:44,680 --> 01:41:47,680
<i>Regardless,</i>
<i>the boys have to push themselves.</i>

2161
01:41:47,760 --> 01:41:49,720
<i>If they want to avoid the Black Room.</i>

2162
01:41:49,800 --> 01:41:51,520
Keep fighting, Mile.

2163
01:41:51,600 --> 01:41:53,440
I challenge both teams.

2164
01:41:53,520 --> 01:41:56,080
Next round, it's a three-way battle.

2165
01:41:56,160 --> 01:41:58,640
Why did Fox have to leave?

2166
01:41:58,720 --> 01:42:01,200
My job is to eliminate.

2167
01:42:02,240 --> 01:42:03,640
Not to explain.

2168
01:42:03,720 --> 01:42:05,160
Oh.

2169
01:42:05,240 --> 01:42:09,280
You ruined a boy's future.
Holding a grudge like this seems personal.

2170
01:42:09,360 --> 01:42:10,400
Don't involve him.

2171
01:42:10,480 --> 01:42:12,560
All right, let's go.

2172
01:42:12,640 --> 01:42:13,600
<i>Back to the room.</i>

2173
01:42:13,680 --> 01:42:15,120
That's the Big Boss.

2174
01:42:15,200 --> 01:42:18,520
My mom got bullied too much last round.
Now my dad is here.

2175
01:42:18,600 --> 01:42:21,520
He stirred the pot and walked away.
This is fun.

2176
01:42:21,600 --> 01:42:24,880
Why do I feel like the winner? Did we win?

2177
01:42:25,640 --> 01:42:26,960
We won, right?

2178
01:42:27,040 --> 01:42:31,240
I haven't done much, but my team
is still fully intact. What should I do?

2179
01:42:31,320 --> 01:42:34,480
No, I want Mile to try harder.
If he did, I wouldn't say anything.

2180
01:42:34,560 --> 01:42:35,840
Honestly, I don't see it.

2181
01:42:35,920 --> 01:42:38,200
Do you want to lose
your member next round?

2182
01:42:38,280 --> 01:42:39,720
When Mile goes to the beach,

2183
01:42:39,800 --> 01:42:43,840
even the sound of the waves
tells him to fight.

2184
01:42:43,920 --> 01:42:46,960
<i>The legendary dining-table runway.</i>

2185
01:42:50,000 --> 01:42:51,120
<i>Table.</i>

2186
01:42:52,680 --> 01:42:53,960
<i>Stop.</i>

2187
01:42:54,040 --> 01:42:55,440
<i>Did you forget to spray it?</i>

2188
01:42:55,520 --> 01:42:57,080
Why are you here?

2189
01:42:57,160 --> 01:42:58,720
To win.

2190
01:42:58,800 --> 01:42:59,920
But maybe not today.

2191
01:43:01,360 --> 01:43:02,320
<i>High heels.</i>

2192
01:43:03,040 --> 01:43:04,040
Who came up with this?

2193
01:43:05,040 --> 01:43:07,760
<i>Make some noise! Make some noise!</i>

2194
01:43:07,840 --> 01:43:10,960
<i>I feel like Donut and Bonus</i>
<i>would make a great ship.</i>

2195
01:43:11,680 --> 01:43:12,520
Dobo.

2196
01:43:12,600 --> 01:43:13,960
To be continued.

2197
01:43:18,200 --> 01:43:20,200
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
